Name: Tomb Maiden

Name: Gear

It can be seen that the level of mobilization for magical creatures not from the Fantasy Library has increased significantly.

Name: Wiznoll

The fact that she tried to utilize the magical creatures that live in the 2nd dimension between the bookshelves is unconventional. For instance, Raphindal and Lapinel are known to have rarely left their pages before Giltine's intervention.

Some even served Vaivora. However, Medzio Diena and the aftermath changed everything.
Name: Raphindion

Description: It is a relief that this monster does not look too different from a normal rat beside the fact that it is contaminated.
Name: Corrupt Mouse

Description: The very embodiment of a demonic world prison guard.
Name: Masked Jailer

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Slime

Description: Nebulas is a Demon Lord working under Demon King Kartas that was famous for bloodshed no matter what the mission was. It is said that no demons like Nebulas since Nebulas was a human that became a demon. Nebulas even has a hatred for Demon King Kartas which is kept in check by certain constraints. Some speculate that if only we could make Nebulas remember her past, we might be able to make a deal with her.
Name: Nebulas

Description: The Tormenta has strong characteristics and values which make it unlikely for it to have mutated during Medzio Diena. It has sadistic tendencies which are believed to be due to it originating from a plant which makes it numb towards pain and the ferocity gained during Medzio Diena.
Name: Tormenta

Description: A mutant-type monster which is raised in demonic world prisons.
Name: Underground Guard Dog

Description: A prison guard in the demonic world. Many high ranking demons are put in the prisons making life difficult for them.
Name: Frightened Prison Guard

Description: It is speculated that these are captured humans turned into demons that are slaving away.
Name: Catapult Slave

Description: There are of course normal books in the Goddess' Fantasy Library. However, there are also many that are made of materials unknown to humans. Lapinels live in the 2nd dimension that is located between the bookshelves that contain such books. They spread to many worlds once they pop out of their books.
Name: Lapinel

Description: Some people used to think these monsters received very little influence from Medzio Diena, when in fact they have developed to a great degree.
Name: Maggot

Description: Oh you poor wanderer whom has many burdens of sin balanced on your back.. part of a poem given to Gorkas by the previous Sage Master.
Name: Gorkas

Description: Dullahan was one of the ghosts that was known to the human world and there were some kinds among them that do not harm people that are not related to the resentment. But, as you know, Medzio Diena changed everything.
Name: Dullahan

Description: Monster
Name: Varv for Directing

Description: This is basically a weapon that gained life turned into a monster.
Name: Morningstar Golem

Description: A low ranking demon that does not have much practicality due to the fact that most high ranking demons can see very well in the dark. It is still placed in the homes of high ranking demons for decorative purposes and the like.
Name: Devil Lantern

Description: The leading theory is that they were humans that died before becoming demons.
Name: Ghoul

Description: Nobody really knows what this particular demon does.
Name: Deathbell

Description: It is unknownn what type of animal this monster consumes in order to obtain its eyes.
Name: Wild Carnivore

Description: This monster is the creation of Demon Lord Naktis and almost reaches the level of an actual Demon Lord itself.
Name: Glutton

Description: There's a legend were Riteris was one of the masters in the past. Among the masters that are not wizards, some make contracts with the demons for immortality and look for others who are similar to them, then lead them to the demon realm.
Name: Blue Riteris

Description: There's a legend were Riteris was one of the masters in the past. Among the masters that are not wizards, some make contracts with the demons for immortality and look for others who are similar to them, then lead them to the demon realm.
Name: Brown Riteris

Description: He has four strong arms. If you don't be careful, you may receive major damage.
Name: Mandara

Description: This info might not be useful to you in real battles, but this monster is very weak against other demons.
Name: Grinender

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.
Name: Tala Wizard

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Archers have been affected more by demons, at least in theory.
Name: Tala Archer

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about.
Name: Tala Battle Boss

Description: The Lyecorn is a monster that transformed from a fossilized plant and is therefore very unique.
Name: Lyecorn

Description: Lakhorn are monsters that appeared from the underworld where humans are not able to go to and have managed to emerge above ground.
Name: Lakhorn

Description: Lakhtanon are said to have been born in underground lakes or rivers. However, there are traces of civilization on them. There are people that say that this is because humans used to live underground a long time ago.
Name: Lakhtanon

Description: Lakhof are minerals from underground rivers that transformed on Medzio Diena. They have managed to come above ground since then.
Name: Lakhof

Description: The Lakhof is a monster derived from a mineral that had been near an underground spring. It came aboveground after Medzio Diena. Those of this color were affected by sulphur when they were underground.
Name: Orange Lakhof

Description: They had been left on the demon's side when the goddesses and demons set the new boundaries. They still have their old look about them, but their personalities have become much more demon like.
Name: Bunkeyto

Description: The Tuthrycon will be able to live anywhere as long as it doesn't get pushed aside by it's competition. It's large mouth and teeth will allow it to obtain food easily.
Name: Tuthrycon

Description: The Nukhalong will occasionally eat other plant type monsters. This is more like vegetation using other plants as fertilizer than the hunting of predators.
Name: Nukhalong

Description: Although it is covered in leaves, this monster had started as steel ore that transformed on Medzio Diena.
Name: Horned Golem

Description: When the Goddess' and demons were dividing borders, they were left on the demon's side simply by coincidence. While they have retained similar appearances, their personalities have already become in-sync with demons. They even play shamanic roles to demons that live in the outer areas. Normally known to assist other demons in preparing for Giltine's rituals.
Name: Romplenuka

Description: There are quite a few animals that gained the ability to fly when they transformed to monsters. Some say that this was due to their boredom of life on the ground.
Name: Mourningbird

Description: It has become stronger in exchange for losing its limbs when transforming into a monster.
Name: Nabu

Description: It seems as if the Kurmis will become extinct due to it becoming too toxic when it mutated into a large monster during Medzio Diena. Of course, it might be okay if the demons start tending to it, but there haven't been any attempts as far as we know.
Name: Kurmis

Description: They had been left on the demon's side when the goddesses and demons set the new boundaries. They still have their old look about them, but their personalities have become much more demon like.
Name: Bunkeybo

Description: It thrives in cold weather despite being an insect after transforming into a monster.
Name: Mouringaka

Description: The most characteristic difference between the Starlakhan and other demons is that it is under the influence of Demon God Raghana. Of course, Raghana is still serving under Giltine.
Name: Starlakhan

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Assassin

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Mage

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Spearman

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Archer

Description: People like to think that the Vylkhas are hostile towards humans. The fact is, Vylkhas dislike all that are not it's own species. Vylkhas Fighters even dislike their own.
Name: Vilkas Fighter

Description: It is unknown when Lucy were first affected by the mysterious powers in the Fantasy Library. However, as soon as the Lucy became something more than mere rabbits, they started cooperating with the demons. Humans were able to feel this tendency after Medzio Diena.
Name: Lucy

Description: Monster
Name: Companion Box

Description: Evoniphon has been known to be the world's best assassin for a long time. He is also widely recognized as the assassin behind the assassination of the Scharffen Star leader. While this made him famous, it also caused the Hunter Master and Ranger Master, both from the Astral Tower, and their apprentices to hunt him. Despite being tracked by these skilled individuals, he was always one step ahead and even managed to assassinate the Chancellor. Whoever takes him down will relieve the world of a burden.
Name: Assassin Ebonypawn

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Guardian

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Iron Maiden

Description: According to legend, Minos used to fight between themselves. This is because the demon lords used to use them to keep the Minos of other demon lords in check. Minos that are treated well by high ranking demons are this color.
Name: Green Minos

Description: It is more accurate to say that the Bavon levitates rather than flies. Bavon of this color have plant-like characteristics which means that it can go a long while without eating.
Name: Green Bavon

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Green Rubblem

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Green Flamme

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Green Flamme Mage

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Green Zolem

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Green Flamag

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Green Flamme Archer

Description: A type of demon summoned by Vubbe at the bidding of demons. It also appears where there are no Vubbe through unknown means. Those of this color cannot live for more than a year.
Name: Green Wood Goblin

Description: They had started to form a union when Gesti received the mission from Giltine to chase after the revelation. Since Medzio Diena, Flammes were created until then and their subspecies were dispatched to various places according to their creator, Gesti's order.
Name: Green Flak

Description: They had started to form a union when Gesti received the mission from Giltine to chase after the revelation. Since Medzio Diena, Flammes were created until then and their subspecies were dispatched to various places according to their creator, Gesti's order.
Name: Green Flamil

Description: A monster derived from a demonic world frog. It is hard to speculate what the original form might have been due to the heavy mutation. This protective color helps if survive.
Name: Green Charog

Description: It's unsure that the demons ignore these monsters and use for the firewood by sacrificing.
Name: Green Charcoal Walker

Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.
Name: Green Blindlem

Description: There are surprisingly few monsters that are derived from fruits. The Leafnut is such a monster. Some Leafnuts fulfill their roles as fruits when they die, but Yellow Leafnuts contaminate the ground making it impossible for vegetation to grow there.
Name: Yellow Leafnut

Description: Grummer can spew extremely toxic fumes that last a long time. As such, special care is required. Grummer of this color have poison from leaf mold.
Name: Orange Grummer

Description: They show tribunal characteristics which is exceptional among Plant-type monsters. In an academic point of view, many people wonder whether they would possess more sociality. Older Colimen turn this color.
Name: Red Colimen

Description: It looks like it doesn't have any sharp edges, but you might be surprised when fighting it. This color of Caro will hide underground during cold weather.
Name: Yellow Caro

Description: Take a look at the Doyor if you want to know what a moving poisonous mushroom looks like. Doyor of this color will live for 2 or 3 years.
Name: Blue Doyor

Description: Tanu are insect-eating plants that have mutated to be meat-eating plants. Tanu of this color have long life expectancies for such plants.
Name: Blue Tanu

Description: Polibu eat small animals, insects and even dead bodies. They even attack humans to simply have one bite so you should be cautious. Polibu of this color hibernate.
Name: Yellow Polibu

Description: It is commonly thought to be a monster derived from a hedgehog, but nobody is quite certain. There are quite a few scholars that suggest it is derived from vegetation. Gosaru of this color live longer than average.
Name: Blue Gosaru

Description: A poet had once said that this monster is the fruition of a flower petal's dream of flying. Upon hearing this, the Sage Master said something of knowing when to be poetic and when to run. Beetow of this color are usually domesticated.
Name: Blue Beetow

Description: While it's appearance hasn't changed much, it's characteristics have changed dramatically. Does not need to live near water anymore. Some have become this color after eating vegetation on land.
Name: Red Ducky

Description: A beast that thrives even in the demonic world which is now terrorizing our world. Those suffering from the side effects of dimensional travel are of this color.
Name: Blue Moglan

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Green Ellomago

Description: A monster summoned by demonic world Shamans by using a Luwa. There are also unconfirmed rumors that they used a Wood Spirit. Those of this color are usually summoned by powerful Shaman even if they are weak.
Name: Blue Woodluwa

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Green Goblin Warrior

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Green Goblin Charger

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Green Goblin Wizard

Description: Medzio Diena changed environments to be more hospitable towards Goblins. They have grown in numbers to the point of taking over much of what used to be human territory. Wood Goblins have nothing to do with normal Goblins. Goblin Shamans held advisory roles in Goblin society even before Medzio Diena.
Name: Green Goblin Shaman

Description: A monster made by demons using a Goddess Statue that has lost it's divine powers. Those of this color are usually made from statues that had been in shady areas.
Name: Black Shardstatue

Description: Lower ranking demons in the demonic world that have a strong desire to rise through the ranks. These Templeslaves will soon be promoted.
Name: Black Templeslave

Description: Lower ranking demons in the demonic world that have a strong desire to rise through the ranks. These Templeslaves will soon be promoted.
Name: Black Temple Slave Assassin

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. They have been forced to come to our world by Giltine who listened to the complaints of all the demons that had been bullied by the Pag who had had Demon King Kartas covering for them. You will regret having a mouth if you are caught by Pag Dopers. Dopers of this color are even worse since they will even spread the liquid over their victims.
Name: Blue Pag Doper

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. They have been forced to come to our world by Giltine who listened to the complaints of all the demons that had been bullied by the Pag who had had Demon King Kartas covering for them. Pag Clampers usually transport their victims or finish them off. Clampers of this color are usually from the Brimstonia region.
Name: Yellow Pag Clamper

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. They have been forced to come to our world by Giltine who listened to the complaints of all the demons that had been bullied by the Pag who had had Demon King Kartas covering for them. Pag Nurses are like this. 'It has to be alive to be tortured, doesn't it?' It is said that Kartas likes this color of Pag Nurse.
Name: Green Pag Nurse

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. They have been forced to come to our world by Giltine who listened to the complaints of all the demons that had been bullied by the Pag who had had Demon King Kartas covering for them. Pag Shearers are one of the most important Pags???hich usually start the procedures on their victims. Those from the Brimstonia region are this color.
Name: Yellow Pag Shearer

Description: The fruits of a Maize look quite appetizing. Of course, you will be poisoned if you actually eat any. Such fruits become this color if nobody actually picks them.
Name: Red Maize

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are usually older than the rest.
Name: Red Siaulav

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are infested by fungi.
Name: Black Siaulav Archer

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are infested by fungi.
Name: Black Siaulav Mage

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Red Slime

Description: While it can't see, it is much more agile than it looks since it has great hearing and smelling capabilities. Those that have been strongly affected by demons are of this color.
Name: Yellow Arma

Description: The Pyran are born from reptilian eggs that are buried under ash. Those from Brimstonia are this color.
Name: Yellow Pyran

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Red Wizard Shaman Doll

Description: The Madakia were created by court wizards to fend off intruders that were more dangerous than grave robbers. It is based on the forceful summoning of dark magic. Black Madakia are one of the strongest and their full might can be seen when fighting demons.
Name: Black Madakia

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated.
Name: Black High Vubbe

Description: Vubbe Archers specialize in using ranged weapons. Thus some people claim the Vubbes have specific roles.
Name: Black High Vubbe Archer

Description: The Wheelen is one of many magical creations made to protect the sealed tombs that have no current overseer. Those with powerful magic are of this color.
Name: Blue Wheelen

Description: A smaller version of a golem that has been affected by demons and has started attacking humans. Those that have been affected by magic are of this color.
Name: Blue Golemlet

Description: Werewolves have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Werewolf

Description: This monster is the creation of Demon Lord Naktis and almost reaches the level of an actual Demon Lord itself.
Name: Glutton

Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.
Name: Mothstem

Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.
Name: Moyabruka

Description: Basically, It was born in the cold region, after Medzio Diena, it is actively working around because spotted in many areas.
Name: Saltistter

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Gremlin

Description: The Froster Lord is a reagent for a world destroyed by Giltine that has frozen over.
Name: Froster Lord

Description: Usually referred to as a monster that returned from the dead. In reality, it underwent death to be reborn as a demon.
Name: Fake Deadborn Boss

Description: Turtai is not on the same side with any goddess. Turtai always wants to strive for its benefits and to accomplish that, it betrays its own species or its allies. But, since there's nothing that humans can provide, there is no way that they would cooperate with humans.
Name: Turtai

Description: Among the spirits of the forest, it is sad that the ones who were most close to the humans became the enemies of the humans.
Name: Centaurus

Description: This monster is the creation of Demon Lord Naktis and almost reaches the level of an actual Demon Lord itself.
Name: White Glutton

Description: Progola???ack sociability, even for a demon. They are forced to work by stronger demons. Before Medzio Diena, they used to hide in order to escape this forced labor.
Name: Progola

Description: After Medzio Diena, some roots and stalks have taken a leg-like appearance giving the monsters a spider-like form. It can't be completely disregarded since it does resemble a spider, despite the disparity in the number of legs.
Name: Event Honey Spider

Description: Demon Lord Hauberk signed a secret treaty with Agailla Flurry, who is known as one of the greatest mages in the history, but after that treaty had been discovered by Demon Lord Helgasercle, the body of Hauberk was ripped into pieces and those pieces were sealed away and scattered across the world. Nevertheless, Hauberk still influences his servants and dreams of his resurrection and return.
Name: Demon Lord Hauberk

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated.
Name: Guardian High Vubbe

Description: Monster
Name: Fake Observation Orb

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Skeleton Archer

Description: As can be seen from the Torrellodeer, monsters derived from beasts that had been caged vary wildly from those that had been in the wilderness.
Name: Torrellodeer

Description: The Rodejokel is a foot soldier of the Rode society.
Name: Rodejokel

Description: The Nuttabug has extremely slow metabolism and will search for a new fruit when it devours it's current fruit. It will die if it cannot find a suitable fruit in time, but this is extremely rare due to it's slow metabolism.
Name: Nuttabug

Description: The Rhodenabean are the common folk in the Rhode society and will use whatever is in their hands as weapons.
Name: Rhodenabean

Description: Rhodenags are usually workers. They use their tools to pick fruit or work the soil.
Name: Rhodenag

Description: They are mainly specialized workers of the Rhode, but will sometimes use attacks related to their work.
Name: Rhodetad

Description: Usually storage keepers for the Rhode.
Name: Elder Rhode

Description: They are treated the worst in the Rhode society. They like to compensate for that by decorating themselves in lavish ways.
Name: Rhodedoe

Description: They can be seen as the freaks of the Rhode society.
Name: Rhodeliot

Description: It is said that the Nuttabug will become Nuttafly???f they manage to survive long enough.
Name: Nuttafly

Description: Administrators for the other Rhode. The human equivalent would be a village elder and they lead a similar amount of subjects.
Name: Rhodevassal

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Tots will never betray anyone that they have a connection to. The issue is that they don't seem to make connections with humans.
Name: Kugheri Tot

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Sommi usually like to be revered by others and will help those that revere them.
Name: Kugheri Sommi

Description: Other Kugheri will often ride or use it to transport luggage.
Name: Kugheri Lyoni

Description: The connection of Numani is incomparable to others. They only respect those that are spiritually stronger than themselves.
Name: Kugheri Numani

Description: There are rumors that say that you will be able to befriend a Symbani if you manage to save its life.
Name: Kugheri Symbani

Description: The Zabbi do the occasional biddings of Kugheri Numani and wait for the chance to become Numani themselves.
Name: Kugheri Zabbi

Description: The mental state of Kugheri Zeuni has not been properly recorded anywhere.
Name: Kugheri Zeuni

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. The only way to resolve a feud with a Balzer is to kill it or be killed.
Name: Kugheri Balzer

Description: The Zeffi are small but have murderous intent behind their every move.
Name: Kugheri Zeffi

Description: This floating witch was deployed to our world by the Demon King Baiga.
Name: Cyaria

Description: The Gardener is a great threat to any human no matter how dull it may appear to be.
Name: Castle Gardener

Description: They are not high ranking demons. In fact, they even play the role of clowns in front of high ranking demons.
Name: Phiro

Description: You might think that the Ragbird doesn't look like much. You may want to think again taking in the fact that it's a demon.
Name: Ragbird

Description: Although it was overshadowed by stronger demons in demon territory, it is showing that it can be a terror of it's own here in our world.
Name: Ragged Butcher

Description: Did they raise crops in the demonic world and were they affected by Medzio Diena? Nobody knows, but it is an interesting topic to think about.
Name: Straw Walker

Description: It is impossible to tell if it is a real scarecrow or a monster. It might look similar because a demon might have imitated a human scarecrow. It might also be a mutation from the demonic world, but nobody knows for certain.
Name: Scarecrow

Description: What passes for a cute puppy in the demonic world is a savage beast by human standards.
Name: Amberdog

Description: A monster that has transformed from a poisonous flower that used to grow in dark places.
Name: Flowlon

Description: Many herbivores had been near their food on Medzio Diena and this caused them to have complex transformations. This is one of those monsters.
Name: Flowlevi

Description: Bloms and Virdneys became monsters through the same process. The only difference is that Virdneys sprouted from the ground.
Name: Virdney

Description: A monster that has transformed from a flower or fruit that was still on its original branch.
Name: Blom

Description: Rumpelstiltskin is the first demon who dealt with the Kedora Merchant Alliance, but Vhaldobas is the demon who dealt with them the most. Vhaldobas had a strong sense of curiosity for a demon and especially so for science and engineering. Vhaldobas did not mind trading with humans. Of course, this doesn't mean that any human can trade with demons.
Name: Vhaldobas

Description: They are not high ranking demons. In fact, they even play the role of clowns in front of high ranking demons. However, demons will sometimes boast that they are simply close to stronger demons.
Name: Pierroll

Description: Before it was revealed to be a mutated plant, it was speculated to be a monster's larva.
Name: Cave Ravinelarva

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Homunculus

Description: They are not high ranking demons. In fact, they even play the role of clowns in front of high ranking demons. While some will boast about being near stronger demons, most dislike grouping up. As such, these demons are looked down upon.
Name: Pingping

Description: They are not high ranking demons. In fact, they even play the role of clowns in front of high ranking demons. They play various clown roles due to the complexity of demon society.
Name: Pamphene

Description: This was a monster that threatened the human society a long time ago. When Roxona turned into a petrified city, there was a rumor that there was a herd of Basilisks.
Name: Fallen City Basilisk

Description: Monster
Name: Advanced Dark Theurge

Description: It was never observed before that a monster which was originally a bug turned into an imago type monster. It shouldn't occur when you look at it.
Name: Ravinepede

Description: Nuaele is one of those low-ranked Demon Lords. Strangely enough many demons follow it so that other Demon Lords do not treat them lightly.
Name: Demon Lord Nuaele

Description: Demon Lord Zaura is a war aficionado and only kneels to stronger opponents. However, he still looks down on them if they are not a type of warrior demon. For instance, Zaura believes that Demon Lord Baiga is weaker because Baiga does not kill the minions of other demon lords for fun. The one exception to this attitude is Giltine.
Name: Demon Lord Zaura

Description: There's nothing special about Demon Lord Blut. But, what is significant about him is that he is the Demon Lord that was randomly picked by Giltine to disturb Laima's prediction.
Name: Demon Lord Blut

Description: Beowolfs have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Werewolf

Description: A monster derived from a sculpture that had magical glyphs or runes etched in them. Those with oxidized steel are of this color.
Name: Red Glyquare

Description: Nothing is known about Anchors except that they are from the demonic world. It is unknown if an object became a monster or if it is a mutated demon. Even the colors do not offer any proper evidence.
Name: Red Anchor

Description: They murder demon soldiers if they get bored. It is said that those of this color are favored by Kartas.
Name: Green Prison Fighter

Description: Rumpelstiltskin is the first demon who dealt with the Kedora Merchant Alliance, but Vhaldobas is the demon who dealt with them the most. Vhaldobas had a strong sense of curiosity for a demon and especially so for science and engineering. Vhaldobas did not mind trading with humans. Of course, this doesn't mean that any human can trade with demons.
Name: Vhaldobas - Fake

Description: Nuka is under the control of the Demon King Baiga and was dispatched here to fulfill the tasks that Gesti received from Giltine. But, Gesti is controlling them unlike what Baiga once thought.
Name: Nuka

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.
Name: Nuo

Description: Elma is one of Gesti's bodyguards, she is dispatched to various duties and also works as a guard at the devil realm.
Name: Elma

Description: A long time ago, Elet used to be a fairy or a soul. They received the curse of Goddess Ausrine and they hid into the human world and lived on. Since Medzio Diena, when the demons invaded the world, they are showing their determination to participate with the other demons.
Name: Elet

Description: All the senses of a Nightshadow Fox Warrior are extremely sensitive. They are said to be capable of picking up all their surroundings without their eyesight.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Warrior

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Assassin

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Mage

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Spearman

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Vilkas Archer

Description: People like to think that the Vylkhas are hostile towards humans. The fact is, Vylkhas dislike all that are not it's own species. Vylkhas Fighters even dislike their own.
Name: Vilkas Fighter

Description: The Lyecorn is a monster that transformed from a fossilized plant and is therefore very unique.
Name: Lyecorn

Description: The Tuthrycon will be able to live anywhere as long as it doesn't get pushed aside by it's competition. It's large mouth and teeth will allow it to obtain food easily.
Name: Tuthrycon

Description: The monster used to be a small and insignificant creature that lurked on swamp bottoms before Medzio Diena. Little is known of it's transformation.
Name: Armaos

Description: Lavenzard are monsters from the demonic world that volunteered to come to our world in order to avoid being trapped as punishment.
Name: Red Lavenzard

Description: Beowolfs have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Lycanthrope

Description: Akhlass type monsters are demons, but originate from our world. The Akhlass Dame is one that has re-transformed after gaining human essence.
Name: Akhlass Dame

Description: The armor of Akhlass Tikke shows what the Tikke wishes to become. The estrangement is somewhat saddening.
Name: Akhlass Tikke

Description: The Akhlass absorb human essence when they become demons. By doing so, they acquire desires that they don't have as bats. The difference is much more stronger among Beorns than Tikke.
Name: Akhlass Beorn

Description: Akhlass Sensors enjoy absorbing and emitting the energy of demons. They become stronger through this process.
Name: Akhlass Sensor

Description: Unlike other Akhlass, the Humps do not have any aspirations related to humans. They believe that humans must cease to exist as there is nothing else to be learned from them.
Name: Akhlass Hump

Description: The Akhlass Petals wish to become a Countess by proving their worth. As such, they also like to order those around as much as they like to fight themselves.
Name: Akhlass Petal

Description: Akhlass Steel have a tendancy to fight as they wish instead of following the orders of others.
Name: Akhlass Steel

Description: The Akhlacia are not as high up the hierarchy as they initially seem. They are more like maids for nobles. In other words, their class is in accordance to their owner.
Name: Akhlacia

Description: All Akhlass Bishops are ambitious and will scheme about climbing the demon social ladder at any chance.
Name: Akhlass Bishop

Description: The Countess has extremely good hearing even among the Akhlass. It is said that they are able to hear conversations that others can't hear.
Name: Akhlass Countess

Description: The Nightshadow Fox Wizard does not use many spells. They prefer to perfect a few spells to the extreme.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Wizard

Description: People that take them lightly for their small size soon regret it.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Cub

Description: Twilight Priests are those that have received their magic from the Demon King Baiga. They obey the Demon Lords while ordering the Nightshadow Fox.
Name: Twilight Priest

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Breaking Wheel

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Storm Calling

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Creeping Death Charm

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Tri-disaster Charm

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Dark Sight

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Henge Stone

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Pear of Anguish

Description: Monster
Name: Observation Orb

Description: There must only be one Akhlass Princess per region. If not, they will battle until there is only one left standing. If there are more than one per region, this is a sure sign of there being an even higher ranking demon controlling them.
Name: Akhlass Princess

Description: The lifespan of a Castle Princess is rarely more than one hundred years. This is unusually short for a demon. As such, they try every method of extending this short lifespan including magic, vampirism, alchemy and much more.
Name: Castle Princess

Description: It's nickname is the one who was swallowed first. According to rumors, it has gained it's current appearance after being swallowed by Gesti and being reincarnated. It is unknown if Diena is actually loyal to Gesti despite following her orders. If Giltine did actually warn Gesti against giving power to Diena, then it might mean that Diena still has a hatred of them. Her name comes from when she was swallowed, during the day.
Name: Demon Lord Diena

Description: This monster is said to move without taking the rider's will into consideration.
Name: Escarot

Description: The Kugheri believe that the world changes based on three different reasons, and how it looks depends on which reason is the strongest. The Kugheri Balzermancer is the leading Kugheri of this faith and is more of a shaman than a priest.
Name: Kugheri Balzermancer

Description: Monster
Name: Rocksodon Companion Box

Description: He has the tendency to control evil spirits and steal the power from those who do not obey him in order to accumulate even greater power.
Name: Necroventer

Description: Compared to the goddesses, the demons either grow or create demons that protect their territories. According to a legend, Cerberus didn't have the form it now has.
Name: Guard Dog Cerberus

Description: Dullahan was one of the ghosts that was known to the human world and there were some kinds among them that do not harm people that are not related to the resentment. But, as you know, Medzio Diena changed everything.
Name: Dullahan

Description: A demon that respects the strong and is cruel to the weak. Nonetheless, its aggression trivializes this characteristic.
Name: Stoulet Archer

Description: Wendigos are known for attacking humans as prey. Wendigo Escapees are thought to be those that have broken away from the group in order to have the prey for themselves.
Name: Wendigo Escapee

Description: A demon that respects the strong and is cruel to the weak. Nonetheless, its aggression trivializes this characteristic.
Name: Stoulet

Description: Colifly are the rookies of the demonic world, only appearing after Medzio Diena. They have yet to find their species specialties and are still in the process of creating societies but aren't looked down upon by other demons. Recently, there have been increases in specimen that have their own proficiencies such as magic.
Name: Black Colifly

Description: Sockets used to live deep underground in our world as well as in the demonic world. It is one of the few monsters that existed before Medzio Diena.
Name: Socket

Description: A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.
Name: Chromadog

Description: Sockets used to live deep underground in our world as well as in the demonic world. It is one of the few monsters that existed before Medzio Diena.
Name: Socket Archer

Description: A demon that respects the strong and is cruel to the weak. Nonetheless, its aggression trivializes this characteristic.
Name: Stoulet Mage

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Red Infrorocktor

Description: A popular theory is that you have to be a demon to use this messenger.
Name: Black Desmodus

Description: A demon minion found throughout the world.
Name: Zigri

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Old Hook

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Blue Slime

Description: A monster derived from a Wizard's personal belongings. It's color varies depending on what it was containing at the time.
Name: Blue Flask

Description: It gets created when the stone pieces or the stone figures of the buildings which the demons stayed change.
Name: Blue Guardian Spider

Description: It is uncertain which roles Belegg is responsible for and whether they are just moving magical creatures.
Name: Belegg

Description: Many creatures have been placed in the Royal Mausoleum, including the Tombsinker, to guard against intruding demons.
Name: Tombsinker

Description: When it comes to flight, Bavon would be better just floating there as is.
Name: Bavon

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated. The number of Vubbe that are able to learn magic after Medzio Diena has greatly increased and their techniques are similar to that of earlier human wizards. It is interesting to see whether they will be able to replicate human Cyromancer techniques.
Name: Vubbe Ice Wizard

Description: The number of Bagworms is no longer increasing, yet its current population is enough not to worry about extinction.
Name: Bagworm

Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.
Name: Hogma Warrior

Description: Though their appearance can be mistaken with other similar-looking monsters, Zinutekas are artificially constructed by magic.
Name: Zinutekas

Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.
Name: Night Maiden

Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.
Name: Dawn Maiden

Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.
Name: Darkness Maiden

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Wizard Shaman Doll

Description: A monster derived from a demonic world frog. It is hard to speculate what the original form might have been due to the heavy mutation.
Name: Charog

Description: It's unsure that the demons ignore these monsters and use for the firewood by sacrificing.
Name: Charcoal Walker

Description: A demon that follows the Demon Lord Hauberk. Most of them still show their loyalty to Hauberk even after their owner was sealed by Helgasercle.
Name: Harugal

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Black Shaman Doll

Description: Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Name: Hallowventer

Description: The name of this monster suits its appearance, but it doesn't reflect its nature at all.
Name: Geppetto

Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.
Name: Shardstatue

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Red Vubbe Fighter

Description: The sister of Pawnd. Carries a scythe that is much taller than itself. It's name depends on where and what it is born of.
Name: Pawndel

Description: A soldier that makes up the army of the demons.
Name: Pawnd

Description: Galok is a monster who command workers in the demon realm.
Name: Galok

Description: Deadborns turn into Rodelins when they receive a lot of influences from demons or when they are acknowledged by the high-ranked demons.
Name: Rodelin

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.
Name: Nuo

Description: A long time ago, Elet used to be a fairy or a soul. They received the curse of Goddess Ausrine and they hid into the human world and lived on. Since Medzio Diena, when the demons invaded the world, they are showing their determination to participate with the other demons.
Name: Elet

Description: There is no meaning of the question that candle to change monster or monster to change candle. Since Medzio Diena, many monsters appeared is target to kill not curiosity.
Name: Candle Spider

Description: In various regions, they created either the Kupoles or the idols of the spirits. Some of them started to work as evil creatures after Medzio Diena.
Name: Malstatue

Description: Shredded is a demon monster that was derived from the by-product that results when you transform a monster into a powerful ghost.
Name: Shredded

Description: When the demons found Glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.
Name: Glizardon

Description: These were originally from our world but became scarce after migrating to the demonic world. Their numbers have been increasing lately. Those that have been affected by ghosts may turn black.
Name: Black Drake

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Infrorocktor

Description: Egnomes carry a stern look. The more stern it looks, the more powerful it is.
Name: Egnome

Description: Despite its appearance, this magical creation has received the blessing of the goddess. Can deal critical damage to demons.
Name: Shtayim

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Kepa

Description: Not a particularly strong monster, but you might end up crying if you attack it without thinking twice. Has a tendency of becoming red as it ages.
Name: Red Kepa

Description: The Kepa is not a strong monster. However, attacking it recklessly may bring you to tears.
Name: Poisoned Kepa

Description: Kepa age quickly at the expense of their strength. Be careful of its pungent odor, which has gotten stronger with age.
Name: Old Kepa

Description: The research to find out why some Kepas transformed to like this is progressing. Even the research to see if it was edible, but still, nothing is certain.
Name: Kepa Chieftain

Description: It is commonly thought to be a monster derived from a hedgehog, but nobody is quite certain. There are quite a few scholars that suggest it is derived from vegetation.
Name: Gosaru

Description: There are rumors saying the Weaver is looking for thread made of stone.
Name: Weaver

Description: Their numbers grew after the Great Plant Cataclysm; now they tend to compete with humans for territory.
Name: Chupacabra

Description: Velcoffer Guards aren't demons, but regular animals that mutated into monsters. What's more, the advent of these beasts wasn't caused by Medzio Diena. The Sage Master speculates that they were one of the monster species said to have been exiled from our world in a joint effort by goddesses and demons. As there are no records of these monsters prior to Medzio Diena, it's possible that the disaster set them free from the seals that detained them.
Name: Velcoffer

Description: It is not uncommon for inanimate objects to become monsters after Medzio Diena, but the appearance of candlesticks on the heads of existing monsters remains a curious phenomenon.
Name: Candle Logger

Description: According to a courageous observer, the two heads often quarrel with each other. If it weren't for their anatomy preventing either head from hurting the other, murder-suicides would likely be a common occurrence.
Name: Porahound

Description: A monster born on Medzio Diena. After discovering these monsters, the demons trained them to pull carriages, and sent those with good combat abilities to the human realm.
Name: Vel's Chariot

Description: Because the venom that Velnipper has is particularly lethal to other insects, it has the upper hand in inter-insect combat. The venom makes many of the insect-type monsters avoid Velnipper. If the Demon King Baiga hadn't suppressed the Velnipper under his command, he wouldn't have faced more insect-type monsters.
Name: Velnipper

Description: A demon under Baiga’s command. Although he has no particular position, he is granted with the most strongest power among other demons as he was born with the extraordinary physical strength. Baiga tamed Jezebel to gain more power. Jezebel became a loyal servant of the Baiga, and nothing but a beast of fear that destroys anything Baiga wishes to get rid of.
Name: Jezebel

Description: For centuries Demon Lord Solcomm has attempted to attack the Astral Tower and Pbeta traveled between the demon realm and our world to aid him. But deep down, Pbeta was dissatisfied and his resentment against Solcomm grew. One day, Pbeta was unable to bear with Solcomm any longer and decided to revolt against him.
Name: Pbeta

Description: Although the Schaffenstar will likely continue to exist, Ignas was the last head of the organization to be entrusted with a Revelation. He not only secretly murdered his predecessor but also manipulated the Demon Lord Solcomm and Pbeta to his own advantage and appropriated the power of a demon monarch. Despite his heinous actions, he was a man of exceptional talent, perhaps even comparable to the founder of the Schaffenstar, Lydia Schaffen.
Name: Ignas

Description: Kabad trampled on the people of the capital city with the plants that turned into monsters on Medzio Diena. At that time, the horns of the Kabad didn't have the same shape of today. Since the day, the shape of the horns has gradually changed, mainly due to the consumption of plant-type monsters and Tree Root Crystals. The reason why only few plant-type monsters are left in the closed city is that Kabad is a big eater.
Name: Quavaad

Description: The fact that this monster still consumes grass even after metamorphosis does not lower its ferocity. Even after Medzio Diena, the grass-eating Wooden Centurion devoured the plant-type monsters that appeared after the disaster. It is said that demons strived to keep Kabad and Wooden Centurion apart whenever there was something edible.
Name: Wooden Centurion

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Loftlem

Description: A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.
Name: Tanu

Description: Animals living in the Royal Mausoleum have been deformed in recent years by the influence of the evil energy.
Name: Vesper

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours.
Name: Lizardman

Description: Amphibians that have branched out and evolved to be able to hunt in arid areas, travelers should be wary of them.
Name: Groll

Description: Stone Orca are a peculiar case even among the monsters to appear after Medzio Deina. They appear as sea-faring creatures that don't have any relation to minerals and appear in areas that are far from the oceans. Nobody has yet solved the mystery behind these monsters.
Name: Stone Orca

Description: The Corylus is a mutant hybrid between plants, animals and minerals.
Name: Corylus

Description: A severely mutated bee and beetle hybrid with qualities of both, it operates in swarms.
Name: Chafperor

Description: The different thing between the normal Golem is that they follow the regular rules. Even current people could not understand it.
Name: Sauga

Description: Compared to other animal species, the Vekarabe didn't change much from their original form when they turned into monsters. However, their aggresion definitely is a new addition.
Name: Vekarabe

Description: The servant and guard of a Demon Lord. They are colored as such because it's their Demon Lord's preferred color.
Name: Red Dawn Maiden

Description: A table for identifying items.
Name: Identification Table

Description: A table for identifying items.
Name: Shadow Condensation

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Echad

Description: Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life
Name: Varv

Description: Many types of Chupacabra have appeared all over the place resulting in massive injuries and destruction of property. The Desert Chupacabra is one of the worst.
Name: Desert Chupacabra

Description: The Boowook are one of the many defensive systems left by Zachariel the Great in the Royal Mausoleum.
Name: Boowook

Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.
Name: Vikaras

Description: It hasn't been discovered yet from which inanimate being this monster tranformed from.
Name: Lemur

Description: Upent rapidly appeared from what once were flora with magical powers.
Name: Upent

Description: The Madakia were created by court wizards to fend off intruders that were more dangerous than grave robbers. It is based on the forceful summoning of dark magic.
Name: Medakia

Description: These guardians were placed in many tombs, starting with the Royal Mausoleum of Zachariel the Great, to stop intruders. Its name came from grave robbers who've encountered them.
Name: Rusrat

Description: They are the monsters that were created from the transformations of stone architectures that were engraved with the letters of magic or runes.
Name: Glyquare

Description: The stone cavalry of the Royal Mausoleum are magical creations made to withstand even the most heavily-armed of knights.
Name: Mauros

Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.
Name: Vikaras Mage

Description: Due to their cute appearances, many people tried to tame Tinis, but they never succeeded.
Name: Blue Tini

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Echad Magician

Description: They show tribunal characteristics which is exceptional among Plant-type monsters. In an academic point of view, many people wonder whether they would possess more sociality. Brown Colimen are in the 'autumn' phase of their lives.
Name: Brown Colimen

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Rubblem

Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.
Name: Blindlem

Description: Many people have tried to tame the Tini because of their cute looks but have all failed. There are many Tini of this color near hot springs or geysers.
Name: Brown Tini Magician

Description: According to legend this watchdog is a creation that Zachariel the Great had planned to preserve.
Name: Venucelos

Description: As Demon Lord Baiga gradually takes on Gesti's legacy, the demons that protected his territory have been appearing more frequently in our world. One example of that is the Tainted Gargoyle.
Name: Tainted Gargoyle

Description: Cave Miniverns are the scavengers of the demon world. They can feed on carcasses, but they tend to hunt other small necrophagous animals. These monsters aren't built to live underground, but they are often spotted in sewers or caves, where they go to hunt.
Name: Cave Minivern

Description: Flowertree is the smartest plant in history. — Appraiser Master Sandra
Name: Flowertree

Description: Its name may be similar to the Mallet Wyvern's, but they are two entirely distinct species.
Name: Wyvern

Description: The difference between other ghost type demons and the Banshee Boss is that she isn't a demon from a human's soul. They originate from humans that were born in the demonic world. Humans are rarely born in the demonic world and are usually killed when they are young. As such, those that live long enough and become ghost type demons are much stronger than the average demon.
Name: Banshee Boss

Description: The name of the monster's weapon became it's name since what other demons call it isn't important to the Kingdom's people. It's interesting to note that the other demons don't like the King Hammer. This is most likely due to the fact that they are under the influence of Demon Lord Hauberk.
Name: King Hammer

Description: Better known as subordinates of Demon King Kartas. Although some monsters tend to change masters with ease, this species is said to dutifully obey every whim of their commandant.
Name: Velcoffaner

Description: The Varle King is the most revered among all Varle. Many Varle King are cooperating with Demon King Kartas in order to widen their realms. Those from the Zealot Order dislike all that have betrayed Goddess Jurate and they especially dislike the Varle Kings.
Name: Varle King

Description: Cave Miniverns are less prone to following orders, preferring to listen to their instinctive needs. Therefore, this species was modified by high-rank demons to play a more specific role in combat. It is slightly stronger and more intelligent than other Miniverns.
Name: Cave Minivern Warrior

Description: Some Cave Minivern Warriors have the ability to draw out magic from their bodies through the process of awakening. These monsters are an example of that.
Name: Cave Minivern Mage

Description: Monster
Name: Velcoffer Prop

Description: Monster
Name: Velcoffer Prop_2

Description: Monster
Name: Velcoffer Prop_3

Description: Solcomm is a Demon Lord that was quite skilled but had the misfortune of meeting a bad leader, a skilled opponent such as Lydia Schaffen, fighting in unfavorable terrain, having bad minions and choosing the wrong allies. In other words, Solcomm was the unluckiest Demon Lord.
Name: Solcomm

Description: This monster obtained its legendary name due to its appearance. Other than that, this monster doesn't have anything special.
Name: Tripede

Description: The Panto have settled and lived in the Gele region for a long time and were even friendly with humans before Medzio Deina. These particular Panto are thought to have ingested plants that have been mutated during Medzio Diena.
Name: Red Panto Spearman

Description: The only good thing that came from the mutation was that the beast became a bit smaller. Also, the fact that someone had managed to capture one doesn't mean that it is any less dangerous. Loxodon of this color have usually feasted on strange food.
Name: Red Loxodon

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Goblin Charger

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Blue Vubbe Fighter

Description: It still tends to gravitate toward rotten flesh.
Name: Kowak

Description: Still has a tendency of going after rotten flesh. Those that have had their blood's color change after Medzio Diena show these colors.
Name: Orange Kowak

Description: The reason why Fishermen are classified as monsters is due to their fishing rods controlling the creatures. Inanimate object Specimen of this color were inanimate objects in an iron-rich environment.
Name: Red Fisherman

Description: Some scholars want to know how grown up Melatinuns are like. But, adventurers, masters and soldiers don't want to know about them and they don't want to see their appearances.
Name: Melatinun

Description: Despite looking quite similar, this monster has nothing to do with the Glass Mole. In fact, this monster is a mutation of a plant.
Name: Pink Root Mole

Description: Wendigo Searcher don't have anything to eat while tracking their targets and will eat their target once they catch them.
Name: Blue Wendigo Searcher

Description: Wendigo Shamans are thought to be able to absorb the powers from their prey. It is not unbelievable when seeing what they are normally up to.
Name: Blue Wendigo Shaman

Description: The Infro Holder is one of the many mutations caused by the appearance of demons. Individual characteristics are becoming much more apparent after Medzio Diena. All Infro Holder colors are based on which demons they are affected by.
Name: Green Infro Holder Shaman

Description: A lesser demon that acts as a sort of everyday object for other demons.
Name: Mirtislampa

Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.
Name: Red Darkness Maiden

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted. Those that were affected by demonic energy are of this color.
Name: Yellow Yognome

Description: It exhibits a much more stern expression than that of a Yognome. It is also that much stronger. Those affected by demons are of this color.
Name: Yellow Egnome

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Yellow Gazing Golem

Description: A somewhat cute mutant that is always expressionless. They assemble together when chanting.
Name: Haze

Description: Griba of this color have the characteristics of a therophyte.
Name: Big Green Griba

Description: It has no relation with the Kepa. They are demonic beasts even if they do have a rather high intelligence.
Name: Kepari Shaman

Description: Griba of this color have the characteristics of a therophyte.
Name: Green Griba

Description: This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.
Name: Blue Cronewt

Description: This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.
Name: Blue Cronewt Poisoned Needler

Description: This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.
Name: Blue Cronewt Magician

Description: The Infro Holder is one of the many mutations caused by the appearance of demons. Individual characteristics are becoming much more apparent after Medzio Diena. All Infro Holder colors are based on which demons they are affected by.
Name: Red Infro Holder

Description: Sockets used to live deep underground in our world as well as in the demonic world. It is one of the few monsters that existed before Medzio Diena. Sockets that have arsenic in their systems are this color.
Name: Green Socket

Description: Sockets used to live deep underground in our world as well as in the demonic world. It is one of the few monsters that existed before Medzio Diena. Sockets that have arsenic in their systems are this color.
Name: Green Socket Mage

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color live for several years.
Name: Blue Siaulav Archer

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color live for several years.
Name: Blue Siaulav

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color live for several years.
Name: Blue Siaulav Mage

Description: Nuka is under the control of the Demon King Baiga and was dispatched here to fulfill the tasks that Gesti received from Giltine. But, Gesti is controlling them unlike what Baiga once thought.
Name: Nuka

Description: Elma is one of Gesti's bodyguards, she is dispatched to various duties and also works as a guard at the devil realm.
Name: Elma

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantegeous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future.
Name: Hohen Gulak

Description: Demon God Baubas has great ambitions on taking over the realm of the Goddess'. Trampler is a loyal minion of Baubas and there are many rumors saying that Trampler will become a Demon Lord soon.
Name: Trampler

Description: Meska Lords are constantly evolving. After living as normal bears, during Medzio Diena they gained special intelligence and strength, becoming powerful monsters that attack other creatures for their energy.
Name: Meska Lord

Description: Lunger Boars appeared after Medzio Diena and they are thought to be manmade monsters. It is the only possible explanation for the strange attachments on their backs.
Name: Lunger Boar

Description: Fealty Hound aren't demons, but beasts originating from our world that evolved into monsters. It is assumed they were created not by Giltine, but by another demon goddess. The Fealty Hounds are therefore loyal to demon goddesses.
Name: Fealty Hound

Description: Amiss Dogs are monsters created artificially during Medzio Diena. Apparently, however, their creator is not satisfied with the results due to unexpected consequences.
Name: Amiss Dog

Description: Quip Mages aren't animals; they are assumed to be cursed humans or failed transmutation experiments.
Name: Quip Mage

Description: Medzio Diena was a fortunate event for Madon Maidens, as they managed to possess different creatures in order to become more powerful. However, it is still uncertain whether their possessing spirit is human or demon.
Name: Madon Maiden

Description: Prodded Horses are a species of unicorn born after Medzio Diena that mutated into a monster.
Name: Prodded Horse

Description: Tel Harshas are one of the many forms a human can take when they are reborn as a demon. It may not be the best form, but the fact they became Tel Harshas means they were once highly respected humans.
Name: Tel Harsha

Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.
Name: Hogma Warrior

Description: Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.
Name: Hogma Archer

Description: While they look like guardsmen, these Hogmas have extensive battle experience.
Name: Hogma Fighter

Description: Succubus are following Demon Lord Naktis' orders, but it is said that they aren't happy with how things are going.
Name: Alluring Succubus

Description: Molich has served several Demon Lords over the centuries and is likely to keep advancing into higher ranks. Experts who have studied demon history predict that, if he does, he could surpass even lower-rank Demon Lords such as Bramble or Mirtis.
Name: Frantic Molich

Description: The Glackuman, who dreams of becoming a famous fighter, is only satisfied if he is dispatched to locations where a lot of fights are taking place.
Name: Rugged Glackuman

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops Mage

Description: Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Name: Hallowventer

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Tots will never betray anyone that they have a connection to. The issue is that they don't seem to make connections with humans.
Name: Kugheri Tot

Description: Other Kugheri will often ride or use it to transport luggage.
Name: Kugheri Lyoni

Description: There are rumors that say that you will be able to befriend a Symbani if you manage to save its life.
Name: Kugheri Symbani

Description: The Zabbi do the occasional biddings of Kugheri Numani and wait for the chance to become Numani themselves.
Name: Kugheri Zabbi

Description: The mental state of Kugheri Zeuni has not been properly recorded anywhere.
Name: Kugheri Zeuni

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Sommi usually like to be revered by others and will help those that revere them.
Name: Kugheri Sommi

Description: People that take them lightly for their small size soon regret it.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Cub

Description: The Nightshadow Fox Wizard does not use many spells. They prefer to perfect a few spells to the extreme.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Wizard

Description: All the senses of a Nightshadow Fox Warrior are extremely sensitive. They are said to be capable of picking up all their surroundings without their eyesight.
Name: Nightshadow Fox Warrior

Description: The Kugheri believe that the world changes based on three different reasons, and how it looks depends on which reason is the strongest. The Kugheri Balzermancer is the leading Kugheri of this faith and is more of a shaman than a priest.
Name: Prodigious Kugheri Balzermancer

Description: Monster
Name: Transparent Object

Description: Only after painful research was it found that this monster had mutated from an animal. While nobody now believes that it is from a plant, it is still being debated on what type of animal it was.
Name: Aphisher

Description: These monsters, which are mutated seaweed, attack all they can see and will follow them if they are stronger. However, it is difficult for land-faring humans or monsters to lead them since they will run into the sea when cornered.
Name: Gob

Description: A female Nimrah. After their mutation, Nimrah males focused only on battle and started to neglect their eggs. This is no different for the Damsel. Oceanographers and other researchers are studying their changed habits, but have yet to find anything solid.
Name: Nimrah Damsel

Description: The Varlefloater is known to trade with humans in extremely rare circumstances. They can tell if the human is reliable enough to trade with but usually deem them unworthy. It is unknown what criteria the Varlefloater uses to analyze their opponents.
Name: Varlefloater

Description: Even the species that had been under Goddess Jurate's influence went their separate ways after mutating into monsters. The Nimrah either started working for the demons or stayed under Jurate's influence on individual levels.
Name: Nimrah Lancer

Description: After Medzio Diena, some Nimrah have ambitions of ruling both the sea and land. They will cooperate with demons and even defy what Goddess Jurate is saying in order to achieve this goal.
Name: Nimrah Soldier

Description: If you are pressed into finding a human society equivalent, the closest thing would be an independent mercenary. Of course, this doesn't mean that the Gunner has no loyalties. Varle social tendencies are difficult for a normal person to understand.
Name: Varle Gunner

Description: The Varle will fight other Varle if not from the same group. The Varle Hench is usually in charge of pioneering and scouting and is normally the first to fall.
Name: Varle Hench

Description: After Medzio Diena, oceanic creatures chose one of three paths whether they had mutated or not. They could still follow Goddess Jurate, cooperate with the demons, or act independently. While the Varle are independent, they had always had a certain dislike for humans making many think that they are cooperating with demons. Varle Skippers are among the leading elite of the Varle society.
Name: Varle Skipper

Description: Despite what they may look and act like, Varle Henchmen are even more important than Varle Skippers. That is because the influence of Varle Skippers are measured in how many Varle Henchmen are following them. As such, a Varle Skipper without any Varle Henchmen is nothing more than an empty flag.
Name: Varle Henchmen

Description: Varle Anchors are usually older Varle, which might seem surprising. Of course, there are younger Varle as well, but this is because they are well experienced. While Anchors will also participate in battle, they are used to show their dominance over a certain area.
Name: Varle Anchor

Description: According to Varle societal rules, the Skipper has seniority over the Helmsman. However, the Helmsman can beat the Skipper to a pulp if the Henchmen support him and choose to lead the group in a different direction. This doesn't mean that the defeated Skipper is exiled. Only Goddess Jurate might understand this madness.
Name: Varle Helmsman

Description: Unlike most other mutated sea creatures, the Kindron were always distant with Goddess Jurate. They used to be the scavengers of the ocean before they mutated during Medzio Diena. There are some that still remain loyal to Goddess Jurate, but most have become hostile towards her.
Name: Kindron Weilder

Description: Used to be a creature that purified water before Medzio Diena. There are currently many that care not for their pasts and have started to leave Goddess Jurate's influence.
Name: Kindron Reilter

Description: This evil demon will do all that it can to torment those weaker than itself even if they are demons. They will even perform mind-control on weaker demons, but the high ranking demons do not seem to care. They wreak havoc when they appear in our world.
Name: Lavisher Mage

Description: Lavishers are all evil, but how they torment their prey depends on an individual level. This particular specimen loves to torment it's prey without saying anything until the prey manages to understand what the Lavisher wants.
Name: Lavisher

Description: A magical levitation stone from the Starlit Lake that turned into a monster during Medzio Diena. It was thought to only exist near Starlit Lake since most of the magical levitation stones throughout human history were used there, but it seems as if the Kedora Merchant Alliance and Agailla Flurry had quite a few of their own.
Name: Lake Golem

Description: Fondus were known to occasionally appear near Starlit Lake even before Medzio Diena. There was a massive increase in their population after Medzio Diena. The liquid on top of the Fondus is an extremely rare foodstuff. It costs a fortune to detoxicate it enough to be fit for human consumption. It may be put back on the tables of nobles if the Schaffen Star manages to recover.
Name: Fondus

Description: The Anchor Golem is a monster that is derived from the linkage in the magical levitation stone.
Name: Anchor Golem

Description: The Lily Velly has the ability to levitate which means it can appear anywhere. However, it likes magical levitation stones and magic-infused water which makes Starlit Lake it's preferred habitat. Its numbers were kept under control when Schaffen Star was active, but those days are far gone.
Name: Lily Velly

Description: The Jelly Velly is dangerous even when it is deactivated. It is said that it can affect the mental state of people that have it close by for too long.
Name: Jelly Velly
