Description: You can see a strong hatred resonating from the otherwise cute Atti. While misfortune is not uncommon post Medzio Diena, it is sad that even vegetation and their fruits are attacking humans.
Name: Atti

Description: The vegetation in the Great Woodlands was not tropical. There was no change in climate after Medzio Diena either. As such, it is a mystery as to why there are so many plant-type monsters in that region. The same can be said to why the Litchiring is found amongst the White Tree Forest.
Name: Litchiring

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yakyak

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yak Shaman

Description: A specimen that is in the process of going through a rite of passage in the Hohen society. Those that have already proven much have black fur.
Name: Black Hohen Barkle

Description: The Hohen Ritter is the backbone of Hohen society regardless of the color of their fur. Although there are times where the Hohen Mane and Mages command them, they have a certain pride that they are the pillars of Hohen society. Remembering that those with black fur have plenty of experience from the demonic world is important.
Name: Black Hohen Ritter

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yak Warrior

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yak Druid

Description: There is a theory about monsters derived from insects after Medzio Diena. Scholars think that insects that mutated under the influence of magic will mutate into only having two eyes instead of the original insectoid eyes. It is believed that the Bush Beetle is such a case, but nobody has managed to get proper evidence to back this theory.
Name: Bush Beetle

Description: While unconfirmed, it is thought that the Blossom Beetle is a form of insectoid undead. If so, the flower on it's back is growing on a carcass.
Name: Blossom Beetle

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantegeous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future.
Name: Black Hohen Gulak

Description: Hohen are a species that had been competing with humans even before the Kingdom but had never been a real threat due to their limited numbers. However, they have started to threaten humans thanks to the environment becoming more favorable after Medzio Diena.
Name: Black Hohen Mane

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yak Mambo

Description: According to legend, the Yak are demons that are looking for a king to succeed the fallen king that they had been contractually bound to. However, the Yak are having a difficult time finding their place in the demonic world as there are no humans that wish to deal with demons in order to rise to the throne.
Name: Yakmap

Description: If you find yourself staring at glaring red eyes in an abandoned building or in a dark forest, it will most likely be a Neuk. Prepare to fight.
Name: Neuk

Description: Started appearing in devastated rural areas but has started spreading since. Thankfully, it does not have high intelligence so it is unlikely to be able to spread too much.
Name: Beur

Description: Hohen Mages are rather new in Hohen society. Demons that had lived in our world rather than the demonic world. Those that had great magical talents grew in number after Medzio Diena and became Hohen Mages. Some Hohen were more active in the demonic world. These specimen are usually black.
Name: Black Hohen Mage

Description: The Great Woodlands are heavily wooded as you might expect. While the concerns of people about the area becoming a home to droves of plant-type monsters has not come to pass, there are still many fruit type monsters that do not appear to be natural. the Mangosting is one such monster.
Name: Mangosting

Description: Despite the fact that it has already been 4 years since Medzio Diena, there are still some people trying to eat monsters that look similar to fruits even if they don't taste good enough to die for. Please don't risk your life to make a Half Mangosting, it isn't worth it.
Name: Half Mangosting

Description: Droopers occasionally feel strong impulses to murder humans and as such are basically serial killers. They are dangerous because nobody has any knowledge on when they feel such impulses.
Name: Drooper

Description: Stone Orca are a peculiar case even among the monsters to appear after Medzio Deina. They appear as sea-faring creatures that don't have any relation to minerals and appear in areas that are far from the oceans. Nobody has yet solved the mystery behind these monsters. The reason this particular Stone Orca is red is because of the oxidized steel.
Name: Red Stone Orca

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantageous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future. Hohen that were more active in the demonic world are black.
Name: Black Hohen Orben

Description: The fact that the Harugal, mavericks of the demonic world are still holding on can be traced back to two reasons. One is the fact that demons don't track down outsiders if they aren't ordered to. The other is because Harugal are quite strong and ferocious. Those that have been in a lot of conflicts in the demonic world have black fur.
Name: Black Harugal

Description: The Oscuro are born high above the demonic world and grow heavier the longer they live. They start living closer to the ground as they do so because the growth rate of their wings is too slow to sustain their flight. They basically crawl on the ground just before they die. While females might be able to temporarily fly higher after they spread their offspring, male Oscuro will never be able to fly as high as they did the day before.
Name: Oscuro

Description: Souls and consciousness are prey of the Claro. Whether in our world or the demonic world, those preyed on by the Claro may appear to be fine but will die quickly due to the lack of soul and consciousness. They will feast on larger prey together. Humans will not be able to return to the Goddess' if they are preyed on by Claro when they die.
Name: Claro

Description: Wherever this monster appears in the world, the fact that it comes from Goddess Vaivora's Fantasy Library is undeniable. However, humans know little about the Fantasy Library and as such little is known about this monster.
Name: Bookmark Mimic

Description: Similar to a Bookmark Mimic. Wherever this monster appears in the world, the fact that it comes from Goddess Vaivora's Fantasy Library is undeniable. However, humans know little about the Fantasy Library and as such little is known about this monster.
Name: Page Mimic

Description: Demons do not deal well with hardship and pain. Of course, there are always exceptions to the rule and there are certain demons that rise above the rest after enduring hardship. The fascinating thing is that the Archless Angel is not such a demon. It is merely the byproduct of chaos.
Name: Archless Angel

Description: The Luna Angel is born during the process of the Archless Angel becoming stronger. Most of the chaos from the Archless Angel is given to the Luna Angel during this process. They become entirely separate entities after this and live their individual lives.
Name: Luna Angel

Description: Never before seen monsters have started appearing in the Fantasy Library after Giltine's infiltration. The Levada is one such monster and the Kupoles are worried that the Levada will spread to the rest of the world.
Name: Levada

Description: The Martybook is also a monster that appeared after Giltine's infiltration. It is said that you might be able to catch a ride on top of it if you are lucky enough.
Name: Martybook

Description: Monster

Crowvasia all have different personalities which means that the only thing the Crowvasia have in common is the fact that they have nothing in common. They are known to follow Hauberk, and this is thought to be because at least one of Hauberk's diverse personalities suit the Crowvasia. There are of course just as many that hate Hauberk for the same reasons. It is difficult for even high ranking demons to utilize Crowvasia on a large scale if they aren't Giltine. It is rumored that Giltine has in fact mobilized many of them recently.
Name: Crowvasia

Description: Most demons prefer chaos over order. Rotascion are one of the most extreme. Only the strongest demons will be able to bend them to their will.
Name: Rotascion

Description: They are not animals nor inanimate objects. They are demons and yet they are not demons. They have souls yet they do not have souls. They are born when chaotic demons such as the Crowvasia or Rotascion hide their souls to objects after defying stronger demons and failing. Of course, they show peculiar traits due to their chaotic souls. As such, it is better to see them as inanimate objects turned into monsters rather than the souls of demons.
Name: Boogey Box

Description: The Cretobien is a demon that was unknown to humans before Medzio Diena. As such, it is speculated that this demon might actually dislike being in our world.
Name: Cretobien

Description: Humans don't know what the Creto do in the demonic world. Some say that they might provide entertainment to higher demons based on their appearance, but this is most likely an error in judgment because demons don't have the same emotions as humans.
Name: Creto

Description: It is a creature that places its origin to the demon realm. It is a kind that is related to Velnewt.
Name: Plokste

Description: The Nimrah Duke are usually leaders of a group. If there are more than one Nimrah Duke in a group, they form an oligarchy in order lead the group.
Name: Nimrah Duke

Description: When the Nimrah Frieker's are not engaged in battle, they mostly hunt. The spoils of the hunt are distributed along the Nimrah hierarchy, so it can be said that they provide food for the whole Nimrah society.
Name: Nimrah Frieker

Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.
Name: Obsidian Golem

Description: Before Medzio Diena, encounters humans rarely encountered Hydras, but when they did, the Hydras were an opponent difficult to face. They are no longer imortal, however, so anyone competent enough should be able to hunt one.
Name: Hydra

Description: Progola???ack sociability, even for a demon. They are forced to work by stronger demons. Before Medzio Diena, they used to hide in order to escape this forced labor.
Name: Progola

Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. When humans see them, they look the same, but they differentiate themselves from each other by having different names so humans also call them differently.
Name: Rafene

Description: As a bird, it is easily attracted to bird feed. Demons use this to make these monsters attack humans.
Name: Sparnas

Description: It is little ambiguous which types of lives become the source of Gaigalas. It is suspicious if they existed in our world.
Name: Gaigalas

Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.
Name: Golem

Description: Current Ginklas is caught by madness, so there is no chance to show his original rationality.
Name: Ginklas

Description: It was never observed before that a monster which was originally a bug turned into an imago type monster. It shouldn't occur when you look at it.
Name: Ravinepede

Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or if they are originally demonic beings. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.
Name: Rajatoad

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Rikaus

Description: It is known that the tail is used when they compete against each other, but you should not just rely on such tendency.
Name: Mallet Wyvern

Description: Even the demons who caused Medzio Diena didn't know the Magburks around them would turn out like this.
Name: Magburk

Description: For unknown reasons, after mutating during Medzio Diena this monster shows high hostility towards the goddesses.
Name: Mushcaria

Description: Some of the monsters have strong powers by changing the format at Medzio Diena tried to make a cooperation with Demon or hired by them.
Name: Bearkaras

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Vubbe Fighter

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Red Vubbe Fighter

Description: Demon Lord Bramble is considered the least ingenious. Gesti, who favors simpler personalities, however, granted him higher authority. Bramble is also believed to have nearly succeeded in seizing a goddess relic, a task where other Demon Lords have failed.
Name: Bramble

Description: Insect-type monsters mutated during Medzio Diena are known to have queens or other monarch entities.
Name: Biteregina

Description: Basically, It was born in the cold region, after Medzio Diena, it is actively working around because spotted in many areas.
Name: Saltistter

Description: Although its name is not unique, this monster in fact will is the most faithful companion of death that you will encounter.
Name: Scorpio

Description: Yekub unleashes its infamous cry in the demon realm, which produces many minions and spreads them around the world. Yekubite is the name given to these minions.
Name: Yekub

Description: The advantage can be found the powerful monsters are that many of them can't move to another place.
Name: Iltiswort

Description: The forest became horror after Medzio Diena. It mainly caused by the large scale monsters to be hard to defeat.
Name: Giant Red Wood Goblin

Description: Although it does not affect humans, this monster strongly dislikes other insect types besides itself, particularly bee-type monsters.
Name: Chafer

Description: The research to find out why some Kepas transformed like this is ongoing. There are also efforts to make them edible, but not many expect positive results.
Name: Kepa Chieftain

Description: Before Medzio Diena, encounters humans rarely encountered Hydras, but when they did, the Hydras were an opponent difficult to face. They are no longer imortal, however, so anyone competent enough should be able to hunt one.
Name: Hydra

Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or if they are originally demonic beings. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.
Name: Rajapearl

Description: Old Status that Goddess' divinity left from here will absorb the demons.
Name: Corrupted

Description: As a bird, it is easily attracted to bird feed. Demons use this to make these monsters attack humans.
Name: Sparnas

Description: Although its name is similar, it is not related to the monsters that turned out from birds.
Name: Sparnasman

Description: Since the Pantos turned their backs on humans, the species that were never seen before appeared. Maybe... the demons are the culprit.
Name: Capria

Description: Prior to Medzio Diena, this monster spent most of its time sleeping, so it wasn't that dangerous.
Name: Nepenthes

Description: Naktis has three sisters who are Demon Lords and they are all related to Demon Queen Gesti.
Name: Naktis

Description: Neop was recently promoted as a Demon Lord by Giltine in order to disturb Laima's plans. Because of the promotion, he tries hard to learn more.
Name: Neop

Description: The Tetraox used to be a beast used in arenas before Medzio Diena. As such, they not only hate Gladiators and Matadors, but ordinary humans as well.
Name: Tetraox

Description: This was a monster that threatened the human society a long time ago. When Roxona turned into a petrified city, there was a rumor that there was a herd of Basilisks.
Name: Basilisk

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Gremlin

Description: Velnewts usually group together and hunt together at the demon realm. But, they think that they are strong enough to act alone in our world so they tend to act individually.
Name: Velnewt

Description: There are many monsters of this kind in the demon realm and the Demon Lord picks the strong ones among them and releases them to our world.
Name: Velpede

Description: Sadly, many strong-spirited people have sided with the demons after Medzio Diena. I believe this is an issue that requires a proper policy of tactical negotiation.
Name: Pyroego

Description: This arrogant monster who betrayed the blessing of Goddess Zemyna is considered a shame to the goddesses.
Name: Lithorex

Description: This cruel lord of the flowers tries to control all lives in the region he controls regardless whether they are animals or plants.
Name: Nuodai

Description: Progola???ack sociability, even for a demon. They are forced to work by stronger demons. Before Medzio Diena, they used to hide in order to escape this forced labor.
Name: Progola

Description: Marionette is a monster that looks familiar, but brings fear from that familiarity.
Name: Marionette

Description: This transformation is now considered ordinary, in a world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.
Name: Crabil

Description: While most fairy or spirit-type creatures have sided not with humans and goddesses but with demons, the small minority that hasn't is currently taking a neutral stance. Genies are one type of such creatures.
Name: Master Genie

Description: Merregina is still under the control of Goddess Jurate, but since the goddesses are not intervening in human matters, it acts individually.
Name: Merregina

Description: This info might not be useful to you in real battles, but this monster is very weak against other demons.
Name: Grinender

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Gazing Golem

Description: The demons are controlling the strong ones among the creatures that turned into monsters on Medzio Diena. Gorgon used to exist even before Medzio Diena, but it's form and the habit is different from the past.
Name: Gorgon

Description: The Glackuman, who dreams of becoming a famous fighter, is only satisfied if he is dispatched to locations where a lot of fights are taking place.
Name: Glackuman

Description: There's a rumor that the monster who Rexipher modified to break into the Royal Mausoleum is the starting point.
Name: Glass Mole

Description: Nederbovine bases its origin on the demon realm. This is not an intelligent demon. It is a beast that is being raised by demons.
Name: Netherbovine

Description: He has the tendency to control evil spirits and steal the power from those who do not obey him in order to accumulate even greater power.
Name: Necroventer

Description: Nuaele is one of those low-ranked Demon Lords. Strangely enough many demons follow it so that other Demon Lords do not treat them lightly.
Name: Nuaele

Description: Usually referred to as a monster that returned from the dead. In reality, it underwent death to be reborn as a demon.
Name: Deadborn

Description: Legend has it that this is an object of an ancient devil whose identity is unknown. According to that legend, even Giltine didn't want to fight against it.
Name: Devilglove

Description: The history of the Deathweaver has long been known to humans. Many are the warriors and mages who perished in their nets of death.
Name: Deathweaver

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Denoptic

Description: Dullahan was one of the ghosts that was known to the human world and there were some kinds among them that do not harm people that are not related to the resentment. But, as you know, Medzio Diena changed everything.
Name: Dullahan

Description: When Rocktortuga first appeared, many soldiers had difficulties retreating due to it's stubborness. As time went by, the weakness on its body was made known, but it's not easy to attack weakness of Rocktortuga.
Name: Rocktortuga

Description: In the past this animal was quite friendly towards humans, but now it's even more dangerous than demons.
Name: Lepus

Description: Rexipher is known as the wisest Demon Lord among all Demon Lords. The reason why he is not active as he should be is because the Demon Queen Gesti doesn't know how to use him effectively. That is good for humans.
Name: Rexipher

Description: When it succeeds in suppressing an opponent, it has the tendency to paralyze the opponent and suck the body fluid of the opponent at a slow pace. After it increases its size, it attacks small-sized opponents to relieve its aggression and not to fulfill its hunger.
Name: Reaverpede

Description: There's a legend were Riteris was one of the masters in the past. Among the masters that are not wizards, some make contracts with the demons for immortality and look for others who are similar to them, then lead them to the demon realm.
Name: Riteris

Description: The theory that Linkrollers move by magical reaction has been proven. However, what's interesting is that this was not designed by anyone, it was simply created naturally around Medzio Diena.
Name: Linkroller

Description: Giltine thought that Demon Queen Gesti was not working as expected as she dispatched the many Demon Lords recently. Marnox is a recent typical Demon Lord.
Name: Marnox

Description: It is unclear whether it was mutated during Medzio Diena or through a Demon Lord ritual. In any case, it was once a useful piece of equipment.
Name: Mineloader

Description: He has four strong arms. If you don't be careful, you may receive major damage.
Name: Mandara

Description: The demons are trying to give the Manticen great power so they can control other insect-type monsters.
Name: Manticen

Description: In theory, this monster's creation is similar to Dullahan. However, the combined object is not a shield.
Name: Mummyghast

Description: The monster which was transformed by demons after combining diverse types of creatures still shows its loyalty to the demons.
Name: Merge

Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.
Name: Mothstem

Description: Among the ones who try to tame many different kinds of birds, many of them are not interested in Moas. Because this bird eats too much.
Name: Moa

Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.
Name: Moyabruka

Description: Humans and monsters have the tendency to harass others that are weaker than them.
Name: Moldyhorn

Description: Molich has served several Demon Lords over the centuries and is likely to keep advancing into higher ranks. Experts who have studied demon history predict that, if he does, he could surpass even lower-rank Demon Lords such as Bramble or Mirtis.
Name: Molich

Description: Minotaurs have existed since a long time ago, and besides the fact that one other species with wings came from it, they remain as violent as they were in the past.
Name: Minotaur

Description: Mirtis is considered a low-ranked Demon Lord of all the others. The reason why is probably because she failed many missions that were given to her from Giltine. On her last mission, she was sealed by a human. Since Medzio Diena, she has now the freedom to catch up on her failed mission.
Name: Mirtis

Description: Humans have attempted to tame these monsters before they grow, but only demons have succeeded in doing so.
Name: Bebraspion

Description: You shouldn't just think of it as a beast of the demons. This monster is actually intelligent!
Name: Velnia Monkey

Description: They are the demons who took care of the garden of high-ranked demons and fruit trees. After Giltine decided to fight against the goddesses, they now participate in battles. Like most other demons, what they do and their battle skills and all are unrelated.
Name: Velorchard

Description: There's nothing special about Demon Lord Blut. But, what is significant about him is that he is the Demon Lord that was randomly picked by Giltine to disturb Laima's prediction.
Name: Blut

Description: The ones who were known as strong warriors in the demon realm stepped into our world because of Giltine's orders.
Name: Cyclops

Description: A monster that already existed before Medzio Diena. It used to have a liking towards humans in the past, but that feeling has faded away in the current times.
Name: Salamander

Description: Shadowgaler was originally a spirit, but it embraced the power of the demons on Medzio Diena.
Name: Shadowgaler

Description: As a monster of mineral-type mutation, it is unclear why it bears resemblance to a whale.
Name: Stone Whale

Description: It was created to protect humans by Dievdirbys Master, but it has been the harmful monsters to change the characteristtics.
Name: Sequoia

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Shnayim

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Specter Monarch

Description: Simorph was reported as the first case that obtained the status of a demon as a monster due to its cooperation. Some masters don't want this to be the example of future unpleasant outcomes.
Name: Simorph

Description: Powerful insect-type monsters tend to become either vicious hunters or influential individuals. The latter group, in which the Throneweaver is included, is particularly dangerous, as they often side with demons.
Name: Throneweaver

Description: There's a rumor going around that Ironbaum used to be the target of practice for the demons. Regardless of what their origin is, they are threats to us now.
Name: Ironbaum

Description: Archon belongs to a high class in the demon realm and he is responsible for many things besides the battles.
Name: Archon

Description: At first, they were created accidentally through the abuse of magic, but later malicious wizards and demons started creating them intentionally.
Name: Abomination

Description: It is the creation of magic that mages and humans frequently used to protect their treasures.
Name: Unknocker

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Achat

Description: Ellaganos are undead creatures that become fused with their gravestones and emerge after a long period of time possessing enormous power.
Name: Ellaganos

Description: Yeti was just a legend prior to Medzio Diena and it's appearance was discovered only recently which led to it's acknowledgment as a monster.
Name: Yeti

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Yonazolem

Description: They can be called the Bokors of the demon realm. It is possible that they interact with Giltine and use the authority.
Name: Wood Houngan

Description: Werewolves have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Werewolf

Description: The Divine Tree, which was the rest place for the goddesses, became their enemy.
Name: Unicorn

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Zaura

Description: An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appears even in areas where Vubbes are not found.
Name: Giant Wood Goblin

Description: It is known that Chapparitions were being created when the spirits of dead mages fell into evil deeds.
Name: Chapparition

Description: Many monsters created lots of diverse transformations on Medzio Diena, but Carapace is unique among them. It was created from the shell which was molted from other animals.
Name: Carapace

Description: The transformation of the Canceril is now considered ordinary, in a world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.
Name: Canceril

Description: Among the spirits of the forest, it is sad that the ones who were most close to the humans became the enemies of the humans.
Name: Centaurus

Description: Compared to the goddesses, the demons either grow or create demons that protect their territories. According to a legend, Cerberus didn't have the form it now has.
Name: Cerberus

Description: Initially, many people underestimated Colimencia, a strong Plant-type monster, since it was in a state of inactivity, but they received severe damage.
Name: Colimencia

Description: Rexipher tried many times to infiltrate into the royal tomb. He didn't succeed the infiltration, but he was able to make a monster called Kubas.
Name: Kubas

Description: It likes to hide in dark places or deep forests. It is timid so it only appears and attacks when it thinks the opponent is weak.
Name: Clymen

Description: Kirmeleech sucks the blood of either monsters or demons since humans are too small for them. However, they do not attack humans, so it's actually not important whether they suck blood from humans or not.
Name: Kirmeleech

Description: The most dramatic change the Goblin society experienced on Medzio Diena was the appearances of strong creatures like the Templeshooter. However, they prioritize their individual benefits more than the Goblin tribe. Even if they serve others, there's a certain possibility that they have hidden purposes.
Name: Templeshooter

Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.
Name: Tutu

Description: A long time ago, he was the hidden guardian who used to protect graves from robbers.
Name: Tomb Lord

Description: This monster who betrayed Goddess Gabija can be called the heretic of the spirits.
Name: Fire Lord

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Ferret Marauder

Description: Poata is trying to find chances to showoff to the demons to obtain more power from the monsters originated plants.
Name: Poata

Description: Violence and cruelty is normal in this place so it's a perfect place for demons. They enjoyed tortures and killings in the demon realm.
Name: Prison Cutter

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Flammidus

Description: It is a creature that places its origin to the demon realm. It is a kind that is related to Velnewt.
Name: Plokste

Description: Though it is a legend that cannot be confirmed, but Harpeia used to follow Goddess Laima instead of the demons.
Name: Harpeia

Description: It became ever more difficult for Goddess Austeja to look over this task, and so this type of monsters started to appear.
Name: Honeypin

Description: Helgasercle used to be one of the strongest Demon Lords out there. Hauberk who was also the Demon Lord who received her wrath and was sealed after she showed her powers. It is not strange that Agailla Flurry is praised by many as the greatest mage in history since she fought against Helgasercle for hundreds of years and won.
Name: Helgasercle

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Specter of Deceit

Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.
Name: Gray Golem

Description: Due to their cute appearances, many people tried to tame Tinis, but they never succeeded.
Name: Tini

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Old Hook

Description: While it has maintained its original form, Operor has developed severely aggressive and violent behavior.
Name: Operor

Description: The Terra Imp is quite mischievous. One should be aware of their belongings, as they might steal them.
Name: Terra Imp

Description: This plant's leaves are stronger than leather.
Name: Green Rafflesia

Description: Jukotail doesn't walk on its tail. It is floating in the air and their insides are empty. We don't know if their insides are emptied within a short period of time after they die.
Name: Jukotail

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantegeous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future.
Name: Green Hohen Orben

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantegeous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future.
Name: Red Hohen Orben

Description: The Big Cockatrice is quite dangerous, as its glare and breath can petrify any opponent. Engaging this creature should not be taken lightly.
Name: Red Cockat

Description: For reasons unknown, this monster holds an extreme hatred towards humans. It prefers to attack humans rather than hunt more suitable prey, or even care about its own survival.
Name: Truffle

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Ragbird

Description: Because of its appearance, novice miners often try to mine the crystal on the spider's back and are attacked.
Name: Crystal Spider

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.
Name: Blue Nuo

Description: Warpulis is one that gets along nicely with Demon King Kartas as they both have fickle personalities. It seems as if Chaos itself has worked itself into this being as Warpulis is ready to sneer at it's opponents while brutally attacking them. As such, no other Demon Lord is interested in keeping Warpulis as a minion. Only Demon King Kartas seems to be able to handle Warpulis.
Name: Demon Lord Warpulis

Description: There are of course normal books in the Goddess' Fantasy Library. However, there are also many that are made of materials unknown to humans. Lapinels live in the 2nd dimension that is located between the bookshelves that contain such books. They spread to many worlds once they pop out of their books.
Name: Lapinel

Description: The Ribbon Raphindal is not much different from a normal Raphindal. The fact that they were deeply moved by the fact that Giltine tied a ribbon on them is not something that other people can easily understand.
Name: Ribbon Raphindal

Description: The Raphindion had lived between the bookshelves of the Fantasy Library before. Vaivora and the Kupoles never made too much effort it catching it because it was prone to hide in the 2nd dimension between the shelves and since it wasn't really harming anyone. Some even served Vaivora. However, Medzio Diena and the aftermath changed everything.
Name: Raphindion

Description: Succubus are following Demon Lord Naktis' orders, but it is said that they aren't happy with how things are going.
Name: Succubus

Description: Stone Frosters are monsters derived from steel, limestone and moss that were on the seashore. We have yet to see the many variations of this monster.
Name: Stone Froster

Description: Oh you poor wanderer whom has many burdens of sin balanced on your back.. part of a poem given to Gorkas by the previous Sage Master.
Name: Gorkas

Description: Lavenzard are monsters from the demonic world that volunteered to come to our world in order to avoid being trapped as punishment.
Name: Lavenzard

Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. When humans see them, they look the same, but they differentiate themselves from each other by having different names so humans also call them differently.
Name: Rafene

Description: The monster used to be a small and insignificant creature that lurked on swamp bottoms before Medzio Diena. Little is known of it's transformation.
Name: Armaos

Description: The Froster Lord is a reagent for a world destroyed by Giltine that has frozen over.
Name: Froster Lord

Description: Each Woodspirit has various personalities. Unlike the outline color, there are various it such as solo play and demon's pawn. But, there are no Woodspirit which have a like to a human.
Name: Woodspirit

Description: Monster
Name: Christmas Sled Box

Description: Although Teal Specter is dead, Medzio Diena has allowed his spirit to remain. Due to the strong magic he possessed in life, his spirit has a different composition from that of other specters.
Name: Teal Specter

Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.
Name: Shardstatue

Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.
Name: Velcoffer Stone Statue

Description: Better known as subordinates of Demon King Kartas. Although some monsters tend to change masters with ease, this species is said to dutifully obey every whim of their commandant.
Name: Velcoffaner

Description: An unnamed Master is known to have said that if there was a bit of intervention from the Goddess', some monsters may have fought for the humans. The main example of such a monster is the Taumas. Unlike the Goddess', the demons were successful in bringing many monsters to their side.
Name: Terra Taumas

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Terra Gremlin

Description: It is known that the tail is used when they compete against each other, but you should not just rely on such tendency.
Name: Terra Mallet Wyvern

Description: It is little ambiguous which types of lives become the source of Gaigalas. It is suspicious if they existed in our world.
Name: Terra Gaigalas

Description: Monster

Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.
Name: Tala Wizard

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Archers have been affected more by demons, at least in theory.
Name: Tala Archer

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about.
Name: Tala Battle Boss

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about.
Name: Sealed Stone

Description: Old Status that Goddess' divinity left from here will absorb the demons.
Name: Ominous Stone Statue

Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.
Name: Shardstatue

Description: The theory is that it's a Gaigalas that hasn't fully grown. However, it is difficult to determine whether this is true because we don't have information on what a Gaigalas was mutated from.
Name: Infrogalas Mage

Description: The theory is that it's a Gaigalas that hasn't fully grown. However, it is difficult to determine whether this is true because we don't have information on what a Gaigalas was mutated from.
Name: Iron Gates

Description: Many people are participating on the efforts to prevent them from producing offspring by spurting out spores.
Name: Terra Rytaswort

Description: The Akhlass Petals wish to become a Countess by proving their worth. As such, they also like to order those around as much as they like to fight themselves.
Name: Akhlass Petal

Description: Akhlass Steel have a tendancy to fight as they wish instead of following the orders of others.
Name: Akhlass Steel

Description: The Akhlacia are not as high up the hierarchy as they initially seem. They are more like maids for nobles. In other words, their class is in accordance to their owner.
Name: Akhlacia

Description: All Akhlass Bishops are ambitious and will scheme about climbing the demon social ladder at any chance.
Name: Akhlass Bishop

Description: The Countess has extremely good hearing even among the Akhlass. It is said that they are able to hear conversations that others can't hear.
Name: Akhlass Countess

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Tots will never betray anyone that they have a connection to. The issue is that they don't seem to make connections with humans.
Name: Kugheri Tot

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Sommi usually like to be revered by others and will help those that revere them.
Name: Kugheri Sommi

Description: Other Kugheri will often ride or use it to transport luggage.
Name: Kugheri Lyoni

Description: The connection of Numani is incomparable to others. They only respect those that are spiritually stronger than themselves.
Name: Kugheri Numani

Description: The mental state of Kugheri Zeuni has not been properly recorded anywhere.
Name: Kugheri Zeuni

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. The only way to resolve a feud with a Balzer is to kill it or be killed.
Name: Kugheri Balzer

Description: Monster
The Rodejokel is a foot soldier of the Rode society.
Name: Rodejokel

Description: The Rhodenabean are the common folk in the Rhode society and will use whatever is in their hands as weapons.
Name: Rhodenabean

Description: Rhodenags are usually workers. They use their tools to pick fruit or work the soil.
Name: Rhodenag

Description: Monster born of the combination of magic stones and lake plants. Before Medzio Diena, they were spotted once every ten years on average. Now, they have increased in number and their population has become more difficult to control.
Name: Lotuscat

Description: Pates are known to appear in lakes when the quality of the water is low. These monsters existed prior to Medzio Diena.
Name: Pate

Description: Coteries live in groups across all kinds of aquatic habitats, from ocean trenches to continental freshwater bodies.
Name: Coterie

Description: Lilly Maids existed prior to Medzio Diena. Before the Schaffenstar began producing chemical baits for them, they were known to lure and drown local lake dwellers.
Name: Lilly Maid

Description: These monsters were once curbstones in the demon world that came to life when Demon Lord Solcomm enchanted them to become part of his troops.
Name: Spinacho

Description: Rubetas are an extremely prolific species. Despite being the most commonly hunted monster in the heydays of the Schaffenstar, they continue to prosper after Medzio Diena.
Name: Rubeta

Description: Little Rubetas can be frequently spotted after Medzio Diena. They did exist prior to that, but Rubetas develop quickly enough that it was rare to come across an infant. Nowadays, their growing numbers have made young Rubetas more common than ever.
Name: Little Rubeta

Description: Long ago, it was thought that Noli Maids buried the lower half of their bodies under rocks to camouflage as flowers. Now we know that their roots gain mobility as the Maids turns into adults.
Name: Noli Maid

Description: Curiously, some Kindron have been known to live in fresh water after Medzio Diena. They are found not only in estuaries but far from the sea in continental lakes as well.
Name: Beissen

Description: Before Ignas took control of the Astral Tower, the water of the Starlit Lake was lethal to demons. To solve this, Demon Lord Solcomm created the Mutts and commanded them to construct a passageway through the lake.
Name: Mutt

Description: Nastes are the materialization of Astral Tower Schaffenstar members transformed under the influence of the demons. Ignas controls their minds, forcing them to obey him.
Name: Naste

Description: Like Mad Lenses, Gleam Lens monsters were once magic lenses left behind by Lydia Schaffen that transformed under the effects of Medzio Diena.
Name: Gleam Lens

Description: Rabblers and Punters are closely related creatures that serve in the demon world as both livestock and hunting companions.
Name: Rabbler

Description: Rumors tell that Wryers were once used as companions by Schaffenstar hunters before they became too ferocious and turned into monsters.
Name: Wryer

Description: Nasleias are former Schaffenstar members that were transformed by magic to serve Ignas. It is said that they have no recollection of their lives as humans.
Name: Nasleia

Description: Like Gleam Lenses, Mad Lens monsters were once magic lenses left behind by Lydia Schaffen that transformed under the effects of Medzio Diena.
Name: Mad Lens

Description: Grobs are thought to have been used by Ignas in his battles against the Resistance army, or by Solcomm in his attacks against the Schaffenstar. In either case, we know these monsters were introduced to the lake for combat purposes.
Name: Grob

Description: Some believe that Hafters may have once been the handles of telescopes placed around the Astral Tower. Conducting research at the Schaffenstar is impossible, however, so this hypothesis has never been confirmed.
Name: Hafter

Description: One could wonder where all these wooden barrels could have come from to transform into monsters, but the truth is that they are a common object found in any human assemblage.
Name: Waglog

Description: The Astral Tower is independently governed by the Schaffenstar, so research on the monsters that inhabit it is scarce. Because of this, we do not know whether Glove Golems appeared due to Medzio Diena or if Ignas created them voluntarily.
Name: Glove Golem

Description: These monsters were brought into the Astral Tower after Ignas joined sides with the demons. They are said to inhabit extreme locations in the demon realm.
Name: Punter

Description: These creatures turned into monsters and began walking upright after Medzio Diena. Unable to return to their underground habitats, they began to hunt on the surface.
Name: Moltooth

Description: Besides the fact that they originate from the demon realm, little is known about Bishopstars. Perhaps more will be revealed when future humans explore the demon world.
Name: Bishop Star

Description: These monsters were pieces of furniture from the Fallen City that came to life after Medzio Diena. Many are the wooden objects that became monsters after that tragic day.
Name: Wajak Walker

Description: Horong Walkers were born of a strange mutation involving will-o'-the-wisps.
Name: Horong Walker

Description: Bishop Grays are said to be the clerics of the demon world, serving the Demon Goddess Ragana.
Name: Bishop Gray

Description: Bishop Points are under the command of demon-world clerics who serve the Demon Goddess Ragana. Although she is only a minor figure in the demon realm, Ragana doesn't seem to cherish them as her followers.
Name: Bishop Point

Description: Kigles are monsters transformed from small-scale secret weapons of the Royal Army.
Name: Kigle

Description: Kigles are monsters transformed from secret weapons of the Royal Army, after their magic began to react to the events of Medzio Diena. After that, General Lhamin halted the production of the weapons, and nowadays they are longer found in the Royal Army.
Name: Kigle Lops

Description: Bishop Blancos are said to perform the role of altar servers to Demon Goddess Ragana. That is only an analogy, of course, as there is no direct equivalent in the human world.
Name: Bishop Blanco

Description: Bishop Harts are demon-world clerics under the command of demon religious orders who serve Demon Goddess Ragana.
Name: Bishop Hart

Description: Poncers are at the top of the food chain in their habitat. They can easily take down a human soldier and, despite their power, they are known to attack only in large groups, making them virtually invincible. Their small stature, however, means that they can become targets to other strong creatures when they are alone.
Name: Poncer

Description: Species in the Yishon family were once nocturnal animals that lived in groups, until Medzio Diena turned them into monsters.
Name: Yishoneer

Description: Species in the Yishon family were once nocturnal animals that lived in groups, until Medzio Diena turned them into monsters. Some became active during the daytime and lost their eyesight, but at the same time they learned to use simple tools.
Name: Yishon Torcher

Description: Cave Stonacorns originated from plant seeds mixed in the excrements of bats and other creatures.
Name: Cave Stonacorn

Description: Solcomm is a Demon Lord that was quite skilled but had the misfortune of meeting a bad leader, a skilled opponent such as Lydia Schaffen, fighting in unfavorable terrain, having bad minions and choosing the wrong allies. In other words, Solcomm was the unluckiest Demon Lord.
Name: Demon Lord Solcomm

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Solcomm Summon

Description: Kindron Leaders are called that because they tend to stand at the front in battles. Unlike their moniker, however, their position is rather low in the Kindron hierarchy.
Name: Kindron Leader

Description: All Kindron species that adapted to freshwater habitats eventually separated from Goddess Jurate. At sea, there are still Kindrons who follow the goddess, although they constitute a minority.
Name: Kindron Boor

Description: Most people believe Humming Dukes to be a gruesome hybrid species that combines mosquitoes and insects created after Medzio Diena.
Name: Humming Duke

Description: These monsters were responsible for leading the negotiations of the Night Panto agreement. We know for sure that Night Pantos entered the Astral Tower after the agreement, although it is still uncertain how they arrived in the Fallen City. The contents of that agreement also remain unknown.
Name: Night Panto Mage

Description: In his efforts to annihilate the Resistance, Ignas acquired the Pipis before Medzio Diena and hatched them to serve in his own army.
Name: Pipi

Description: Well-grown Piangs become Vesperas. According to rumors, they once helped Ignas gain the upper hand in a battle against the Resistance.
Name: Vespera

Description: These monsters settled in the Kingdom's capital after it became a site of ruins. Because of that, they suffered little influence from Medzio Diena and have maintained most of their original form.
Name: Beetlegreen

Description: Besides the larger body, Bumblegreens have remained mostly unchanged since Medzio Diena. That said, they have become incredibly adaptable to new environments.
Name: Bumblegreen

Description: It is said that Night Panto Archers are set to receive access to the archery secrets in the Astral Tower after the end of their contract. Alas, that which they covet the most will never be theirs.
Name: Night Panto Archer

Description: Ignas created the Nastudeu by cursing members of the Schaffenstar with his own blood and transforming them. Unlike Nastes and Nasleias, however, theoretically it should be impossible to return the Nastudeu to their original form.
Name: Nastudeu

Description: An unknown agreement of cooperation with the demons is known to have given special powers to a large number of Pantos, which have since changed into a new appearance. Although the other party in the agreement is not a demon, they are suspected to work in conjunction with them.
Name: Night Panto Stellar

Description: Pipis who hatch become Piangs. Their stages of development are said to apply differently in the demon realm.
Name: Piang

Description: Mushutas transformed from mushrooms grown in cold regions. In northern provinces of the Kingdom, local sayings warn against mushrooms grown under the aurora. Many believe these monsters appeared at the Starlit Lake due to its starlight-attracting properties.
Name: Mushuta

Description: Most small Insect types exist in large numbers. Trippies are an exception, as their populations are smaller than those of similarly-sized species.
Name: Trippy

Description: A tree of ice.
Name: Ice Tree

Description: The Froster Lord is a reagent for a world destroyed by Giltine that has frozen over.
Name: Froster Lord Reflection

Description: Bloks just appeared within the last year, so there isn't much information about it yet.
Name: Blok Archer

Description: Bloks just appeared within the last year, so there isn't much information about it yet.
Name: Blok Magician

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops Mage

Description: There are quite a few reckless people who are going after the monsters that have big ores like the Kenol attached onto the bodies of the monsters. It would have been better if they had acted more cautiously when thinking about the disaster that was brought to the world.
Name: Kenol

Description: The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.
Name: Leafly

Description: Neop was recently promoted as a Demon Lord by Giltine in order to disturb Laima's plans. Because of the promotion, he tries hard to learn more.
Name: Neop

Description: A magical levitation stone from the Starlit Lake that turned into a monster during Medzio Diena. It was thought to only exist near Starlit Lake since most of the magical levitation stones throughout human history were used there, but it seems as if the Kedora Merchant Alliance and Agailla Flurry had quite a few of their own.
Name: Lake Golem

Description: Fondus were known to occasionally appear near Starlit Lake even before Medzio Diena. There was a massive increase in their population after Medzio Diena. The liquid on top of the Fondus is an extremely rare foodstuff. It costs a fortune to detoxicate it enough to be fit for human consumption. It may be put back on the tables of nobles if the Schaffen Star manages to recover.
Name: Fondus

Description: If you are pressed into finding a human society equivalent, the closest thing would be an independent mercenary. Of course, this doesn't mean that the Gunner has no loyalties. Varle social tendencies are difficult for a normal person to understand.
Name: Varle Gunner

Description: The Varle will fight other Varle if not from the same group. The Varle Hench is usually in charge of pioneering and scouting and is normally the first to fall.
Name: Varle Hench

Description: After Medzio Diena, oceanic creatures chose one of three paths whether they had mutated or not. They could still follow Goddess Jurate, cooperate with the demons, or act independently. While the Varle are independent, they had always had a certain dislike for humans making many think that they are cooperating with demons. Varle Skippers are among the leading elite of the Varle society.
Name: Varle Skipper

Description: Despite what they may look and act like, Varle Henchmen are even more important than Varle Skippers. That is because the influence of Varle Skippers are measured in how many Varle Henchmen are following them. As such, a Varle Skipper without any Varle Henchmen is nothing more than an empty flag.
Name: Varle Henchmen

Description: Varle Anchors are usually older Varle, which might seem surprising. Of course, there are younger Varle as well, but this is because they are well experienced. While Anchors will also participate in battle, they are used to show their dominance over a certain area.
Name: Varle Anchor

Description: According to Varle societal rules, the Skipper has seniority over the Helmsman. However, the Helmsman can beat the Skipper to a pulp if the Henchmen support him and choose to lead the group in a different direction. This doesn't mean that the defeated Skipper is exiled. Only Goddess Jurate might understand this madness.
Name: Varle Helmsman

Description: The Anchor Golem is a monster that is derived from the linkage in the magical levitation stone.
Name: Anchor Golem

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.
Name: Tala Wizard

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Archers have been affected more by demons, at least in theory.
Name: Tala Archer

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about.
Name: Tala Battle Boss

Description: Lakhorn are monsters that appeared from the underworld where humans are not able to go to and have managed to emerge above ground.
Name: Lakhorn

Description: Lakhtanon are said to have been born in underground lakes or rivers. However, there are traces of civilization on them. There are people that say that this is because humans used to live underground a long time ago.
Name: Lakhtanon

Description: Lakhof are minerals from underground rivers that transformed on Medzio Diena. They have managed to come above ground since then.
Name: Lakhof

Description: It is more accurate to say that the Bavon levitates rather than flies. Bavon of this color have plant-like characteristics which means that it can go a long while without eating.
Name: Green Bavon

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Green Rubblem

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Green Zolem

Description: In the past, Nicopolis wizards grew these magic creatures by winding the springs on their backs to generate vines, which they used for gardening. After the accident of Nicopolis, however, they were affected by Medzio Diena and became the monsters they are today.
Name: Vine Walker

Description: A few monster experiments created by the wizards of old Nicopolis have begun to reappear after Medzio Diena. Considering how commonly Moyas are used in experiments, Crescent Moyas are likely one of the species' many varieties.
Name: Crescent Moya

Description: Before their mysterious disappearance, the wizards of Nicopolis were known to conduct various experiments on monsters. One of those monsters was the species we now call Wiza Moya.
Name: Wiza Moya

Description: Most of these monsters are old residents of Nicopolis who turned into slime. After a tragic experiment caused them all to disappear, Medzio Diena caused many to return to our world in the form of slime.
Name: Slime Witch

Description: Curiously, some Kindron have been known to live in fresh water after Medzio Diena. They are found not only in estuaries but far from the sea in continental lakes as well.
Name: Kindron Shooter

Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.
Name: Tutu

Description: The Asiomage the Quipmage's other self, created during a failed magic experiment which intended to combine wild magic monsters with docile animals in order to control magic creatures.
Name: Asiomage

Description: Vesperias are the last stage of development of their species. These monsters could have caused serious damage to the Resistance army, if it weren't for the Masters' timely support.
Name: Vesperia

Description: For generations, the wizards of Nicopolis experimented with all sorts of magic creatures. Mimorats were the products of their first experiments on common rats.
Name: Mimorat Purple

Description: Mimorat Whites were created to carry goods on their backs. Even after the wizards of Nicopolis disappeared, these Mimorats survived and have since developed tastes of their own.
Name: Mimorat White

Description: Mimorat Pinks have evolved from Mimorat Whites according to the tastes of the species. Pinks like to collect and carry all sorts of objects, with some objects becoming more popular than others in light of the latest trends.
Name: Mimorat Pink

Description: Greens suffered the most radical transformations out of all the Mimorats after Medzio Diena. There is no telling why some were more affected than others, especially considering that all Mimorats belong to the same species.
Name: Mimorat Green

Description: These creatures were created as prisons according to the tastes of Nicopolis wizards. They became abandoned after the great accident, then turned into the monsters they are today with the influence of Medzio Diena.
Name: Haunted House

Description: These Nicopolis wizards who disappeared after the great accident and returned to our world as slime also lost their arms in the process, so they created a pair of slime arms that move by telekinesis. After that, they continued to conduct experiments and managed to cause another major accident.
Name: Slime Wizard

Description: These creatures originate from a failed experiment of a Nicopolis wizard who attempted to produce easy-to-read magic books. A cute mistake in the history of the city.
Name: Popup Cat

Description: Slime Gemini are the product of a failed experiment by Nicopolis wizards who returned to our world as slime and attempted to regain their human form by cloning themselves. Most residents of Nicopolis who were lost in the great accident and reappeared after Medzio Diena aren't very pleasant to look at.
Name: Slime Gemini

Description: In the past, Nicopolis wizards grew these magic creatures by winding the springs on their backs to generate vines, which they used for gardening. After the accident of Nicopolis, however, they were affected by Medzio Diena and became the monsters they are today.
Name: Vine Walker

Description: Most of these monsters are old residents of Nicopolis who turned into slime. After a tragic experiment caused them all to disappear, Medzio Diena caused many to return to our world in the form of slime.
Name: Slime Witch

Description: The Varle King is the most revered among all Varle. Many Varle King are cooperating with Demon King Kartas in order to widen their realms. Those from the Zealot Order dislike all that have betrayed Goddess Jurate and they especially dislike the Varle Kings.
Name: Varle King

Description: These Nicopolis wizards who disappeared after the great accident and returned to our world as slime also lost their arms in the process, so they created a pair of slime arms that move by telekinesis. After that, they continued to conduct experiments and managed to cause another major accident.
Name: Slime Wizard

Description: These Nicopolis wizards who disappeared after the great accident and returned to our world as slime also lost their arms in the process, so they created a pair of slime arms that move by telekinesis. After that, they continued to conduct experiments and managed to cause another major accident.
Name: Slime Wizard

Description: She was one of the three wizards who ruled Nicopolis. After eliminating the capital and the court with a magic that affects only living beings, her ambitious experiments failed and caused the disappearance of all the residents of Nicopolis. She remained dormant in the form of dead matter, until the events of Medzio Diena brought her back to life.
Name: Pervading Queen

Description: Velcoffer Guards aren't demons, but regular animals that mutated into monsters. What's more, the advent of these beasts wasn't caused by Medzio Diena. The Sage Master speculates that they were one of the monster species said to have been exiled from our world in a joint effort by goddesses and demons. As there are no records of these monsters prior to Medzio Diena, it's possible that the disaster set them free from the seals that detained them.
Name: Velcoffer

Description: Slime Gemini are the product of a failed experiment by Nicopolis wizards who returned to our world as slime and attempted to regain their human form by cloning themselves. Most residents of Nicopolis who were lost in the great accident and reappeared after Medzio Diena aren't very pleasant to look at.
Name: Slime Gemini

Description: The Wastrel is a monster created during the great accident of Nicopolis. Its greatest power is the ability to absorb all kinds of magic in the world.
Name: Wastrel

Description: The Wastrel is a monster created during the great accident of Nicopolis. Its greatest power is the ability to absorb all kinds of magic in the world.
Name: Wastrel

Description: These creatures were created as prisons according to the tastes of Nicopolis wizards. They became abandoned after the great accident, then turned into the monsters they are today with the influence of Medzio Diena.
Name: Mimorat White

Description: These creatures were created as prisons according to the tastes of Nicopolis wizards. They became abandoned after the great accident, then turned into the monsters they are today with the influence of Medzio Diena.
Name: Mimorat White

Description: A long time ago, there were times that they were tamed and mounted by humans.
Name: Experimental Silva Griffin

Description: You shouldn't just think of it as a beast of the demons. This monster is actually intelligent!
Name: Experimental Velnia Monkey

Description: He has four strong arms. If you don't be careful, you may receive major damage.
Name: Mandara

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.
Name: Beeteroxia

Description: This monster was bred by the demons and is known for its poisonous abilities.
Name: Red Velwriggler Mage

Description: Ghosts affected by demons often change their appearance in a way similar to this.
Name: Green Apparition

Description: Despite its appearance, this magical creation has received the blessing of the goddess. Can deal critical damage to demons.
Name: Shtayim Mage

Description: Unlike the prejudice of the humans, Lapezards are not Lapes that obtained their current status through long training. Most of them are selected by their breeds and they grow up accordingly and receive the necessary food to become a Lapezard.
Name: Lapezard

Description: Their status is not high among Lapes, but they are most dangerous and they get encountered often. To receive respect from the other Lapes, they act violently to the ones they encounter with.
Name: Lapfighter

Description: For a Lape to Lapflammer, they just need to obtain the weapons they need. But its not that easy since when Lapflammers die, the weapons also get destroyed so its not that easy for the Lapes.
Name: Lapflammer

Description: Lapemiter is a unique occupation that is highly respected, but is also looked down upon among Lapes. A Lapemiter serves a religious role, but the other Lapes don't put great emphasis on religious rituals, so they want a Lapemiter to do their exhausting duty.
Name: Lapemiter

Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. When humans see them, they look the same, but they differentiate themselves from each other by having different names so humans also call them differently.
Name: Lapa Archer

Description: It is not assured that the Lapeman is the undead of a Lape. However, the Lapeman mostly receives respect from the other Lapes.
Name: Lapeman

Description: There has yet to be a case of more than one hundred Maggots appearing from one Maggot Egg as their number is settled at the very last second. As such, it is hard to spot Maggots. Research is underway because a variety of creatures are showing such colors after Medzio Diena.
Name: Egg

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Slime Witch

Description: There has yet to be a case of more than one hundred Maggots appearing from one Maggot Egg as their number is settled at the very last second. As such, it is hard to spot Maggots.
Name: Wastrel Egg

Description: Monster
Name: Summoned Minion

Description: These creatures were created as prisons according to the tastes of Nicopolis wizards. They became abandoned after the great accident, then turned into the monsters they are today with the influence of Medzio Diena.
While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Shaman Doll

Description: In his efforts to annihilate the Resistance, Ignas acquired the Pipis before Medzio Diena and hatched them to serve in his own army.
Name: Pipi

Description: Pipis who hatch become Piangs. Their stages of development are said to apply differently in the demon realm.
Name: Piang

Description: Well-grown Piangs become Vesperas. According to rumors, they once helped Ignas gain the upper hand in a battle against the Resistance.
Name: Vespera

Description: Rumors tell that Wryers were once used as companions by Schaffenstar hunters before they became too ferocious and turned into monsters.
Name: Wryer

Description: Grobs are thought to have been used by Ignas in his battles against the Resistance army, or by Solcomm in his attacks against the Schaffenstar. In either case, we know these monsters were introduced to the lake for combat purposes.
Name: Grob

Description: Rabblers and Punters are closely related creatures that serve in the demon world as both livestock and hunting companions.
Name: Rabbler

Description: Nastes are the materialization of Astral Tower Schaffenstar members transformed under the influence of the demons. Ignas controls their minds, forcing them to obey him.
Name: Naste

Description: Ignas created the Nastudeu by cursing members of the Schaffenstar with his own blood and transforming them. Unlike Nastes and Nasleias, however, theoretically it should be impossible to return the Nastudeu to their original form.
Name: Nastudeu

Description: Nasleias are former Schaffenstar members that were transformed by magic to serve Ignas. It is said that they have no recollection of their lives as humans.
Name: Nasleia

Description: These monsters were brought into the Astral Tower after Ignas joined sides with the demons. They are said to inhabit extreme locations in the demon realm.
Name: Punter

Description: Vesperias are the last stage of development of their species. These monsters could have caused serious damage to the Resistance army, if it weren't for the Masters' timely support.
Name: Vesperia

Description: Prodded Horses are a species of unicorn born after Medzio Diena that mutated into a monster.
Name: Prodded Horse

Description: Although the Schaffenstar will likely continue to exist, Ignas was the last head of the organization to be entrusted with a Revelation. He not only secretly murdered his predecessor but also manipulated the Demon Lord Solcomm and Pbeta to his own advantage and appropriated the power of a demon monarch. Despite his heinous actions, he was a man of exceptional talent, perhaps even comparable to the founder of the Schaffenstar, Lydia Schaffen.
Name: Ignas

Description: Boruta's life was spared by the mercy of Goddess Austeja thousands of years ago. Now that the goddesses have left and Boruta's seal has weakened with Medzio Diena, Boruta is scheming to return to the Kingdom. We need to prevent this from happening, as we already know of the anguish he will unleash upon the world.
Name: Boruta

Description: These monsters were brought into the Astral Tower after Ignas joined sides with the demons. They are said to inhabit extreme locations in the demon realm.
Name: Engulfed Punter

Description: Vesperias are the last stage of development of their species. These monsters could have caused serious damage to the Resistance army, if it weren't for the Masters' timely support.
Name: Electric Vesperia

Description: Boruta's life was spared by the mercy of Goddess Austeja thousands of years ago. Now that the goddesses have left and Boruta's seal has weakened with Medzio Diena, Boruta is scheming to return to the Kingdom. We need to prevent this from happening, as we already know of the anguish he will unleash upon the world.
Name: Boruta

Description: Boruta's life was spared by the mercy of Goddess Austeja thousands of years ago. Now that the goddesses have left and Boruta's seal has weakened with Medzio Diena, Boruta is scheming to return to the Kingdom. We need to prevent this from happening, as we already know of the anguish he will unleash upon the world.
Name: Boruta

Description: Giltine Sprite
Name: Giltine Sprite

Description: No one is yet aware as to how this little bird came to be such a ferocious beast.
Name: Pennamayo

Description: Since Medzio Diena, people have tried to hunt Frocoli to use as a source of food. Although they found out they weren't edible, they found out that their oil could be used to light fires.
Name: Frocoli

Description: Golas are creatures that exist both in our world as well as the demon realm. While the Golas of the demon realm have higher intelligence, Amphibigolas are named so due to their amphibious nature.
Name: Amphibigola

Description: Crabils are big enough as they are but Infro Crabils are even bigger and stronger.
Name: Infro Crabil

Description: It is just a regular spider, only massively enlarged. It is one of the strangest creatures to appear since Medzio Diena in that it is so ordinary in appearance.
Name: Spider

Description: This monster is known to let out a long howl similar to that of a large bull. Some say it even sounds like a wind instrument.
Name: Tooter

Description: Gazers are monsters that are used by Demon King Baiga as his eyes and ears around the world.
Name: Gazer

Description: Ghosnatus are formed from the ghosts of men who used to be murderes.
Name: Ghosnatus

Description: An imprisoned demon that has been set loose in our world for the sole purpose of wreaking havoc.
Name: Greedy Prisoner

Description: Grinender Time Bomb
Name: Grinender Time Bomb

Description: Giltine needed powerful demons in order to interfere in the plans of the Goddess Laima. She had organized the Demon Lords as her very own elite demon army, which Moringponia was a part of. Ever since being elected into the ranks, Moringponia had been after Laima's Revelations under orders from Baiga. Moringponia was elected as a Demon Lord relatively late in comparison to others in her ranks, but seeing that she answers personally to Baiga tells that she is not to be taken lightly because of this.
Name: Moringponia

Description: A monster that mimics Plague Doctors. They execute people instead of curing them.
Name: Puppet M

Description: We do not know the origins of this monster, but it is certain that they are just as cruel and merciless as demons themselves.
Name: Masked Executor

Description: Giltine needed powerful demons in order to interfere in the plans of the Goddess Laima. She had organized the Demon Lords as her very own elite demon army, which Tantalizer was a part of. Tantalizer had since begun working under Kartas, during the time which he had secretly been in contact with Baiga and taking his orders as well.
Name: Tantalizer

Description: Schaffenstar members often make fun of the monster's short legs.
Name: Amacalf

Description: The scholars claim that a different kind of Elavine exists somewhere in this world but they have yet to find any proof of this.
Name: Rudas Elavine

Description: The scholars had long considered Velsoarers to be demons but they have recently come to realize that it is actually a mutated beast of some sort.
Name: Velsoarer
