Description: It is still under debate which plant the spores of a Velpod actually come from.
Name: Velpod

Description: The spores of a Cloverin can be found spread across almost all of the Kingdom, although they are less seldom seen in the northern parts of the Kingdom where the climate is colder.
Name: Cloverin

Description: New plant monsters such as the Rafflet, are being discovered every day in the Great Woodlands, which is a heavily forested area with a sparse population density.
Name: Rafflet

Description: Ghoscandles are formed out of souls of deceased humans. As you can tell from its appearance, only the vilest and the most perverted humans become Ghoscandles after their souls leave their body.
Name: Ghoscandle

Description: Little is known about the Gigglecat, a ghostly demon that lets out a spine chilling giggle every once in a while.
Name: Gigglecat

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Infro Gremlin

Description: They're cute but they can't be tamed nor can they be eaten as food.
Name: Blueberrin

Description: Despite its appearances, Delione does not belong to an independent species of plants but is a mutation of an already known plant species. Many plant monsters like these have begun to appear since Medzio Diena.
Name: Delione

Description: Fragolin is one of the newer monsters that have only recently been found by the adventurers of the Kingdom. Most of these new monsters are found in the areas around the Fallen City.
Name: Fragolin

Description: They say that Chesha Papas are not affected by the force of gravity.
Name: Chesha Papa

Description: It is said that Chesha Venom's poison rots the mind of the victims that are weak willed.
Name: Chesha Venom

Description: Ghosbebes are demons created from souls of humans that had been a clergyman during their lives.
Name: Ghosbebe

Description: Ghoscats are former pets that have become demons. They are lovable pets to demons but are known as vicious murderers to humans.
Name: Ghoscat

Description: Glands always aim for a specific part of the human body when attacking. Because of this, It is believed that this demon has some knowledge of the human anatomy.
Name: Gland

Description: These demons are said to be found mostly in the areas ruled by Baiga as the terrain there is flat.
Name: Grievous Wheel

Description: Banterers are a friendly lot among demons. Unlike other demons, Banterers are known to be friendly amongst demons but their hostility towards humans is not all that different from the other demons.
Name: Banterer

Description: People doubt that they will ever come across any other gargoyles larger than the Arch Gargoyle, aptly named because of their unusually large size. Even if so, their names will probably remain unchanged.
Name: Arch Gargoyle

Description: Despite having been mutated in Medzio Diena, they can still make the sounds they used to make before they were transformed.
Name: Hooter

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. They are equipped with sharp and study metal claws that can rip through almost anything. Just a slight graze from its claw could fatally wound anyone unlucky to have been struck.
Name: Varnaclipse

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. It has one eye on its head that has its view fixed straight ahead but the often missed second eye on its blade allows the monster to look ahead of incoming threats.
Name: Whimeclipse

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. Its staff overflows with evil energy that takes over the will of the wielder over time. Because of this, the Shilleclipse is the most loyal of Skilaclipse's followers.
Name: Shilleclipse

Description: Originally believed to be herbivores, Kisylions have grown a taste for meat since Medzio Deina. They prone to gathering left-over meat than hunt for themselves, but are dangerous creatures nonetheless.
Name: Kisylion

Description: This monster is known to observe the objects around it when it thinks that no one is looking. A scholar has even gone as far as to confirm this by casting an invisibility spell on himself.
Name: Monitor Lizard

Description: These demons are said to be found mostly in the areas ruled by Baiga as the terrain there is flat.
Name: Red Grievous Wheel

Description: Banterers are a friendly lot among demons. Unlike other demons, Banterers are known to be friendly amongst demons but their hostility towards humans is not all that different from the other demons.
Name: Red Banterer

Description: Glands always aim for a specific part of the human body when attacking. Because of this, It is believed that this demon has some knowledge of the human anatomy.
Name: Red Gland

Description: The sewers of the major cities of the Kingdom were well maintained before Medzio Diena. But now the sewers have become a growing pain, providing habitat for mutant monsters such as these.
Name: Chesa Torso

Description: Chesha Riels are believed to be a result of Mutant-type monsters that have been possessed by evil spirits.
Name: Chesha Riel

Description: No one has yet witnessed this monster actually sewing something.
Name: Chesha Needle

Description: It is impossible to tell if it is a real scarecrow or a monster. It might look similar because a demon might have imitated a human scarecrow. It might also be a mutation from the demonic world, but nobody knows for certain.
Name: White Scarecrow

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Skiaclipse

Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.
Name: Tenacious Tutu

Description: Humans and monsters have the tendency to harass others that are weaker than them.
Name: Devious Moldyhorn

Description: It seems as if the Kurmis will become extinct due to it becoming too toxic when it mutated into a large monster during Medzio Diena. Of course, it might be okay if the demons start tending to it, but there haven't been any attempts as far as we know.
Name: Ferocious Kurmis

Description: The difference between other ghost type demons and the Banshee Boss is that she isn't a demon from a human's soul. They originate from humans that were born in the demonic world. Humans are rarely born in the demonic world and are usually killed when they are young. As such, those that live long enough and become ghost type demons are much stronger than the average demon.
Name: General Banshee Boss

Description: A monster born on Medzio Diena. After discovering these monsters, the demons trained them to pull carriages, and sent those with good combat abilities to the human realm.
Name: Deranged Vel's Chariot

Description: Giltine needed powerful demons in order to interfere in the plans of the Goddess Laima. She had organized the Demon Lords as her very own elite demon army, which Moringponia was a part of. Ever since being elected into the ranks, Moringponia had been after Laima's Revelations under orders from Baiga. Moringponia was elected as a Demon Lord relatively late in comparison to others in her ranks, but seeing that she answers personally to Baiga tells that she is not to be taken lightly because of this.
Name: Demon Lord Moringponia

Description: Giltine needed powerful demons in order to interfere in the plans of the Goddess Laima. She had organized the Demon Lords as her very own elite demon army, which Tantalizer was a part of. Tantalizer had since begun working under Kartas, during the time which he had secretly been in contact with Baiga and taking his orders as well.
Name: Demon Lord Tantalizer

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Shackled Skiaclipse

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Shackled Skiaclipse

Description: No one has yet witnessed this monster actually sewing something.
Name: Black Orb

Description: Borutos Miniverns are the scavengers of the demon world. They can feed on carcasses, but they tend to hunt other small necrophagous animals. These monsters aren't built to live underground, but they are often spotted in sewers or caves, where they go to hunt.
Name: Borutos Minivern

Description: Borutos Miniverns are less prone to following orders, preferring to listen to their instinctive needs. Therefore, this species was modified by high-rank demons to play a more specific role in combat. It is slightly stronger and more intelligent than other Miniverns.
Name: Borutos Minivern Warrior

Description: Some Borutos Minivern Warriors have the ability to draw out magic from their bodies through the process of awakening. These monsters are an example of that.
Name: Borutos Minivern Mage

Description: Borutos Rabblers and Punters are closely related creatures that serve in the demon world as both livestock and hunting companions.
Name: Borutos Rabbler

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Skiaclipse

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. They are equipped with sharp and study metal claws that can rip through almost anything. Just a slight graze from its claw could fatally wound anyone unlucky to have been struck.
Name: Varnaclipse

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. It has one eye on its head that has its view fixed straight ahead but the often missed second eye on its blade allows the monster to look ahead of incoming threats.
Name: Whimeclipse

Description: One of Skiaclipse's loyal subordinates. Its staff overflows with evil energy that takes over the will of the wielder over time. Because of this, the Shilleclipse is the most loyal of Skilaclipse's followers.
Name: Shilleclipse

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Shackled Skiaclipse

Description: Boruta's life was spared by the mercy of Goddess Austeja thousands of years ago. Now that the goddesses have left and Boruta's seal has weakened with Medzio Diena, Boruta is scheming to return to the Kingdom. We need to prevent this from happening, as we already know of the anguish he will unleash upon the world.
Name: Boruta

Description: Monster
Name: Little Sunfish

Description: Misrus had been isolated in the Outer Wall Sewers since Medzio Diena. According to a diary of a dead Schaffenstar member found in the sewers, the Chesha had been fearful of Misrus but did not run away as if something even greater than Misrus was keeping them trapped in the sewers. Whatever that creature may be, it must be at least a demon lord or something even greater.
Name: Misrus

Description: A Tiny Tini that has followed you because of its fondness for humans.
Name: Tiny Tini

Description: Curiously, some Kindron have been known to live in fresh water after Medzio Diena. They are found not only in estuaries but far from the sea in continental lakes as well.
Name: Beissen

Description: Giltine needed powerful demons in order to interfere in the plans of the Goddess Laima. She had organized the Demon Lords as her very own elite demon army, which Moringponia was a part of. Ever since being elected into the ranks, Moringponia had been after Laima's Revelations under orders from Baiga. Moringponia was elected as a Demon Lord relatively late in comparison to others in her ranks, but seeing that she answers personally to Baiga tells that she is not to be taken lightly because of this.
Name: Demon Lord Moringponia

Description: It is said that Chesha Venom's poison rots the mind of the victims that are weak willed.
Name: Large Cheshavenom

Description: No one has yet witnessed this monster actually sewing something.
Name: Moring Sphere

Description: The Froster Lord is a reagent for a world destroyed by Giltine that has frozen over.
Name: Froster Lord

Description: The Kugheri believe that the world changes based on three different reasons, and how it looks depends on which reason is the strongest. The Kugheri Balzermancer is the leading Kugheri of this faith and is more of a shaman than a priest.
Name: Prodigious Kugheri Balzermancer

Description: The Asiomage the Quipmage's other self, created during a failed magic experiment which intended to combine wild magic monsters with docile animals in order to control magic creatures.
Name: Asiomage

Description: The Wastrel is a monster created during the great accident of Nicopolis. Its greatest power is the ability to absorb all kinds of magic in the world.
Name: Wastrel

Description: Although the Schaffenstar will likely continue to exist, Ignas was the last head of the organization to be entrusted with a Revelation. He not only secretly murdered his predecessor but also manipulated the Demon Lord Solcomm and Pbeta to his own advantage and appropriated the power of a demon monarch. Despite his heinous actions, he was a man of exceptional talent, perhaps even comparable to the founder of the Schaffenstar, Lydia Schaffen.
Name: Ignas

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Gimmick Fairy

Description: Monster
Name: Life Essence

Description: The Skiaclipse had been waiting for the chance to wreak havoc on the Kingdom under the orders from an unknown demonic being. The Shadowmancer Master had accidentally stumbled into its lair and ended up imprisoning the creature in its lair. Despite this, due to its immense power, it began to slowly break free from the Shadow Master's spell of imprisonment to once again continue on his mission, bringing devastation on the world.
Name: Shackled Skiaclipse

Description: No one has yet witnessed this monster actually sewing something.
Name: Magic Source

Description: It has become stronger in exchange for losing its limbs when transforming into a monster.
Name: Nabu

Description: Not all Akhlass Petal wants to be Akhlass Countesses. Some put priority on developing their skills in their given positions rather than being recognized.
Name: Akhlass Petal Warrior

Description: The combats where you face against the elite demons are bound to be more chaotic. But if you have trained soldiers, the story can be different. Ponta takes advantage of the chaos in the battlefield, and calmly takes the enemies out.
Name: Ponta

Description: Orc Spearmen wield Two-handed weapons. The enormous strength of orcs maximizes the potential of the weapons. The weapons are may called ‘two-handed’ by human, but they wield them in both hands. Orc Spearmen are likely to at the forefront on the battlefield.
Name: Orc Spearman

Description: Orc Peltasts’ performances on the battlefield literally embody the word ‘heavy’. Any ordinary attacks cannot make them lose their defense form. The counterattack followed by a reckless attack on the shield is always fatal to the attacker. If you encounter an Orc Peltast on the battlefield, you must not let your sword land on its shield.
Name: Orc Peltast

Description: An Orc Leader leads a pack of orcs. Only the orcs who never hesitate to to take the lead in battle can earn the title as bellicosity is considered the greatest value in their society. The double-edged axes wielded by Orc Leaders are the first challenge you must overcome on the battlefield.
Name: Orc Leader

Description: The advent of Orc Cannoneer has completely changed the flow of the battlefield. With orc cannoneers, orcs gained confidence in both ranged and melee combats making their foes intimidated.
Name: Oak Cannoneer

Description: Of all the demons who have came from the demonic world, Living Armor is one of the most interesting kind. Both their armor and the basis of birth cannot be explained. Many think that Living Armor was created from the hands of a blacksmith in the demonic world.
Name: Living Armor

Description: Orcs are rarely outnumbered and the survival of the Orc Flagbearers has a huge impact on their morale. As long as the flag of orcs is flapping in the air, orcs never lose the will to fight in battle. For the reason, some Orc Flagbearers often die standing upright.
Name: Orc Flagbearer

Description: Nukas, who have built up a lot of outstanding work in the demonic world, were assigned for more important missions instead of being sent to Gesti.
Name: Nuka Warrior

Description: What's unique about Nuos is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is incredible that Nuos who is under the control of Kartas possess the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons. The aggressive Nuos are likely to decorate themselves.
Name: Nuo Assassin

Description: Monster
Name: Summoned Minion

Description: It thrives in cold weather despite being an insect after transforming into a monster.
Name: Mouringaka

Description: This beast that once exclusively roamed in the demon realm. Nowadays it is found all over the world, endangering other wildlife and humans.
Name: Moglan

Description: There are quite a few animals that gained the ability to fly when they transformed to monsters. Some say that this was due to their boredom of life on the ground.
Name: Mourningbird

Description: Monster
It could be said that such a color comes from fungi latching onto a monster that is already a mutation of a different kind of fungi.
Name: Big Black Griba

Description: Many people are participating on the efforts to prevent them from producing offspring by spurting out spores.
Name: Rytaswort

Description: The most difficult aspect about dealing with these monsters is that they can appear in people's houses unexpectedly.
Name: Mushwort

Description: This monster was once described as hard to block and hard to eat.
Name: Mini Griba

Description: Monster
Name: Ruby Anvil

Description: It thrives in cold weather despite being an insect after transforming into a monster.
Name: Mouringaka

Description: It could be said that such a color comes from fungi latching onto a monster that is already a mutation of a different kind of fungi.
Name: Big Black Griba

Description: Monster
Name: Summoned Minion

Description: Some say they heard the sound of a metal scratching the wall at night when the moon shone cautiously through the narrow streets. Very few of them have seen a gigantic dog with a sickle. Everyone who survived from the unexplainable creature had to lose their colleagues. Until Viskal's identity was revealed to the world, the rumors made many travelers nervous.
Name: Viskal

Description: It wasn't because of Medzio Diena, but because of other forces, that the body of Vilktys had a curious form, being combined with plants. Vilktys silently dispose of the bodies in bloody and maggot-infested places.
Name: Vilktys

Description: It wasn't because of Medzio Diena, but because of other forces, that the body of Trampauld had a curious form, being combined with plants. There are a lot of speculations as to why the hands have completely lost their shape. The myth that Trampaulds’ hands had the most sins when they were punished is considered to be a truth.
Name: Trampauld

Description: People think Ilgarankas are the same kind of orcs, but the two are quite different. Their muscles are dwarfed by the orcs, but their height and long arms separate them from orcs. Compared to orcs, Ilgarankas are more liberal and barbaric. But Ilgananka armies are not to be underestimated.
Name: Ilgaranka

Description: The reason why people cannot look down on small goblins is because of their unique and vicious characters. They are more cruel and ruthless than you can imagine. The Goblin Archers gain a sick pleasure from shooting arrows at victims’ weak spots at a distance.
Name: Bloguz Goblin Archer

Description: Many war-specific orcs find academic knowledge worthless. All they value are blood, victory, battle and honorable death. The orc captains, who lead a group of orcs, have already gone through a number of battles, and built up their empirical knowledge.
Name: Orc Captain

Description: Orc Shamans did not go on the battlefield, but after Medzio Diena, they began to directly join battles under Giltine's command. People often underestimate their abilities as they used to tell fortunes for the tribes or pray for magical powers before battles and consider them to be unhelpful, but the magic powers they perform are menacing. Since their joining battles, many of the dead bodies on the battlefield were found with a look of fear, and without any external injury.
Name: Orc Shaman

Description: The habits and instincts of the beasts have been maintained even as they have undergone many changes living with Bloguz Goblins.
Name: Grey Wolf Chief

Description: They are very similar to ordinary wolves, but they have undergone many physical changes while staying with Bloguz Goblins.
Name: Grey Wolf

Description: Neckos with a great mobility are tasked with scouting and delivering flanking attacks. In forest, their skin color hides them from enemies’ sight. Neckos decorated with red paint are the pursuers for fallen soldiers.
Name: Necko

Description: Demons needed elite soldiers to form a more powerful and menacing army. In particular, Poevita was specialized to neutralize the enemy's defenses and crush the formation.
Name: Poevita

Description: Ausura has a strict character and the demons are suppressed by their duties. Sodinincuz finds it hard to concentrate on something else without keeping her garden clean.
Name: Sodinincuz

Description: Ausura has a strict character and the demons are suppressed by their duties. Once Tarnites begins to clean the floor, they never stop until the floor reflects the sun light.
Name: Tarnite

Description: One of the facts that makes the demon armies more intimidating is that there are also demons that can cast magic spells. In the defenses of the friendly forces, Poanas pour indiscriminate magic spells into the enemy.
Name: Poana

Description: Bloguz Goblins spent a lot of time training wolves to use them for combat. After all, they figured out that not all wolves likes the one riding on them.
Name: Bloguz Goblin Rider

Description: Stagvaluses never know how to scream or step backwards when a few arrows pierce their armor and this why demons decided to have them in their army. As long as Stagvaluses can move their horns and legs, they never stop chasing the foes.
Name: Stagvalus

Description: Solcomm is a Demon Lord that was quite skilled but had the misfortune of meeting a bad leader, a skilled opponent such as Lydia Schaffen, fighting in unfavorable terrain, having bad minions and choosing the wrong allies. In other words, Solcomm was the unluckiest Demon Lord.
Name: Demon Lord Solcomm

Description: Demon Lord Zaura is a war aficionado and only kneels to stronger opponents. However, he still looks down on them if they are not a type of warrior demon. For instance, Zaura believes that Demon Lord Baiga is weaker because Baiga does not kill the minions of other demon lords for fun. The one exception to this attitude is Giltine.
Name: Demon Lord Zaura

Description: Nuaele is one of those low-ranked Demon Lords. Strangely enough many demons follow it so that other Demon Lords do not treat them lightly.
Name: Demon Lord Nuaele

Description: Monster
The Boowook are one of the many defensive systems left by Zachariel the Great in the Royal Mausoleum.
Name: Boowook

Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.
Name: Hogma Warrior

Description: Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.
Name: Hogma Archer

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers. It hasn't been built for more than one thousand years because King Zachariel didn't leave any blueprints, but there are now attempts at reconstructing it due to the Royal Mausoleum being re-opened.
Name: Shaking Achat

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Fluttering Denoptic

Description: Minotaurs have existed since a long time ago, and besides the fact that one other species with wings came from it, they remain as violent as they were in the past.
Name: Excited Minotaur

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Warmed Up Gazing Golem

Description: It likes to hide in dark places or deep forests. It is timid so it only appears and attacks when it thinks the opponent is weak.
Name: Mission Clymen

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers. Some scholars and wizards wish to attempt at reconstructing the Shnayim if the Achat is successfully restored.
Name: Reanimated Shnayim

Description: A long time ago, he was the hidden guardian who used to protect graves from robbers.
Name: Noble Tomb Lord

Description: Vubbe Archers specialize in using ranged weapons. Thus some people claim the Vubbes have specific roles.
Name: Vubbe Archer

Description: The Kedora Merchant Alliance is thinking of ways to make a product out of this monster.
Name: Scap

Description: The souls of liers and crooks turned into monsters in the demonic world end up like this.
Name: Spekull

Description: A lesser demon that acts as a sort of everyday object for other demons.
Name: Mirtislampa

Description: This plant's leaves are stronger than leather.
Name: Rafflesia

Description: The question of whether this is a candle that turned into a monster or whether a monster and candle were transfused is meaningless. The many monsters that came after Medzio Diena are to be killed, not studied. This color of Candle Spider shows that it has been affected by magic.
Name: Blue Candle Spider

Description: Ultanuns have always been flightless birds even before their deformation.
Name: Ultanun

Description: A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.
Name: Tanu

Description: The yellow grass on its body looks supple. But if you touch it, it can be quite painful .
Name: Tipio

Description: If a moving poisonous mushroom makes you anxious, consider Doyor as an example.
Name: Doyor

Description: A Panto variant with distinctively high intelligence. They often show up with the other Panto variants.
Name: Panto Wizard

Description: Usually referred to as a monster that returned from the dead. In reality, it underwent death to be reborn as a demon.
Name: Deadborn of Steel

Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.
Name: Hogma Shaman

Description: When it succeeds in suppressing an opponent, it has the tendency to paralyze the opponent and suck the body fluid of the opponent at a slow pace. After it increases its size, it attacks small-sized opponents to relieve its aggression and not to fulfill its hunger.
Name: Nasty Reaverpede

Description: An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appears even in areas where Vubbes are not found.
Name: Frantic Giant Wood Goblin

Description: Though it is a legend that cannot be confirmed, but Harpeia used to follow Goddess Laima instead of the demons.
Name: Whirlwind Harpeia

Description: They are the demons who took care of the garden of high-ranked demons and fruit trees. After Giltine decided to fight against the goddesses, they now participate in battles. Like most other demons, what they do and their battle skills and all are unrelated.
Name: Bizarre Velorchard

Description: There's a rumor going around that Ironbaum used to be the target of practice for the demons. Regardless of what their origin is, they are threats to us now.
Name: Mission Ironbaum

Description: Unlike popular belief, their role is to make sure that other Hogma???ontinue to fight, not to coordinate attacks.
Name: Hogma Captain

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Blue Slime

Description: A young Rajapearl. The reason it is black is because it came into contact with a ghost during it's growth.
Name: Black Rajapearlite

Description: Adventurers should take special care of their belongings since they have a tendency of pulling pranks. Those that have stayed under the demonic world's sun for too long become this color.
Name: Brown Terra Imp

Description: A long time ago, Elet used to be a fairy or a soul. They received the curse of Goddess Ausrine and they hid into the human world and lived on. Since Medzio Diena, when the demons invaded the world, they are showing their determination to participate with the other demons. Those that successfully assassinated other demons decorate themselves with these colors.
Name: Blue Elet

Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.
Name: Moyabruka

Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.
Name: Mothstem

Description: It is a creature that places its origin to the demon realm. It is a kind that is related to Velnewt.
Name: Plokste

Description: Werewolves have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Werewolf

Description: Due to their cute appearances, many people tried to tame Tinis, but they never succeeded.
Name: Cold Tini

Description: Originally stalks of plants, the Chinency have since evolved to their current form.
Name: Cold Chinency

Description: The Sparnicht appears to live without too much regard to it's life. It's strange since it's numbers don't seem to be dwindling at all.
Name: Cold Sparnicht

Description: Despite its appearance, the Pokubu can be quite ferocious.
Name: Cold Pokubu

Description: A small form of Golem that is harmful to humans because it receives evil influences.
Name: Cold Golemlit

Description: Stone Orca are a peculiar case even among the monsters to appear after Medzio Deina. They appear as sea-faring creatures that don't have any relation to minerals and appear in areas that are far from the oceans. Nobody has yet solved the mystery behind these monsters.
Name: Cold Stone Orca

Description: Demon Lord Hauberk signed a secret treaty with Agailla Flurry, who is known as one of the greatest mages in the history, but after that treaty had been discovered by Demon Lord Helgasercle, the body of Hauberk was ripped into pieces and those pieces were sealed away and scattered across the world. Nevertheless, Hauberk still influences his servants and dreams of his resurrection and return.
Name: Demon Lord Hauberk

Description: There's nothing special about Demon Lord Blut. But, what is significant about him is that he is the Demon Lord that was randomly picked by Giltine to disturb Laima's prediction.
Name: Demon Lord Blut

Description: Mirtis is considered a low-ranked Demon Lord of all the others. The reason why is probably because she failed many missions that were given to her from Giltine. On her last mission, she was sealed by a human. Since Medzio Diena, she has now the freedom to catch up on her failed mission.
Name: Demon Lord Mirtis

Description: Helgasercle used to be one of the strongest Demon Lords out there. Hauberk who was also the Demon Lord who received her wrath and was sealed after she showed her powers. It is not strange that Agailla Flurry is praised by many as the greatest mage in history since she fought against Helgasercle for hundreds of years and won.
Name: Demon Lord Helgasercle

Description: Rexipher is known as the wisest Demon Lord among all Demon Lords. The reason why he is not active as he should be is because the Demon Queen Gesti doesn't know how to use him effectively. That is good for humans.
Name: Demon Lord Rexipher

Description: Monster
Name: Ice Wall

Description: No one has yet witnessed this monster actually sewing something.
Name: Overloaded Sphere

Description: The Jelly Velly is dangerous even when it is deactivated. It is said that it can affect the mental state of people that have it close by for too long.
Name: Cave Jelly Velly

Description: A similar mechanic as to how a Dievdirby's Owl Sculpture spews fire.
Name: Sequoia Flame

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Weekly Boss Dummy Monster

Description: Monster
Name: Paper Box

Description: Monster
Name: Varistor

Description: Monster
Name: Summoned Minion

Description: A common misunderstanding of humans is that they think that the Dievdirbys were created by a mistake. Of course, we all know that is just silly and untrue.
Name: Gargoyle

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Weekly Boss Dummy Monster

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Weekly Boss Dummy Monster

Description: Some that live inland don't believe that a crab of this size could have existed, but the Greentoshell was actually this size even before Medzio Diena. However, it's growth rate has been greatly accelerated and is now able to grow and live almost indefinitely. As such, there are many more Greentoshell that actually grow to be this size.
Name: Dimension Greentoshell

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Dimension Infrorocktor

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated.
Name: Dimension High Vubbe

Description: Because of its appearance, novice miners often try to mine the crystal on the spider's back and are attacked.
Name: Dimension Crystal Spider

Description: Acting as Mirtis' scout minion, these bats once lived throughout the world but have grown into a large threat despite their small bodies.
Name: Dimension Bat

Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.
Name: Dimension Hogma Warrior

Description: Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.
Name: Dimension Hogma Archer

Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.
Name: Dimension Hogma Shaman

Description: It is said that they receive their powers from human souls because they gather toward the injured.
Name: Dimension Ellom

Description: Merog variant. Slight differences in the mutation process differentiates the variety of Merogs.
Name: Dimension Merog Shaman

Description: This reptile monster attacks instinctively but shows as much abilities as its intelligence.
Name: Dimension Merog Stinger

Description: Unlike popular belief, their role is to make sure that other Hogma???ontinue to fight, not to coordinate attacks.
Name: Dimension Hogma Captain

Description: A monster which is said to be created by demons using the Chupacabra.
Name: Dimension Chupaluka

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Dimension Ellomago

Description: It is fierce against other monsters and humans, more so especially with Insect-type monsters.
Name: Dimension Ellogua

Description: Amphibians that have branched out and evolved to be able to hunt in arid areas, travelers should be wary of them.
Name: Dimension Groll

Description: A monster with a habit of baiting and attacking humans.
Name: Dimension Wendigo

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours.
Name: Dimension Lizardman

Description: Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.
Name: Dimension Tama

Description: It has no relation with the Kepa. They are demonic beasts even if they do have a rather high intelligence.
Name: Dimension Kepari

Description: One of the largest changes after the disappearance of the Goddess' is the fact that underwater creatures started to live on land. Their respiratory organs and blood composition have changed as they started to live on land which caused there to be many colors of Kodomor. Their diet has also changed to accommodate for the change in living conditions.
Name: Dimension Kodomor

Description: It still tends to gravitate toward rotten flesh.
Name: Dimension Kowak

Description: It hasn't been discovered yet from which inanimate being this monster tranformed from.
Name: Dimension Lemur

Description: Extremely resistant to the cold just like a Lemur. It may develop a yellowish color due to demonic energies.
Name: Dimension Lemuria

Description: While they look like guardsmen, these Hogmas have extensive battle experience.
Name: Dimension Hogma Soldier

Description: Compared to an average Hogma, they are much stronger, but their intelligence is lower.
Name: Dimension Hogma Scout

Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an aninal with minenal. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.
Name: Dimension Zinute

Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an aninal with minenal. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.
Name: Dimension Lauzinute

Description: Many types of Chupacabra have appeared all over the Kingdom, resulting in massive injuries and destruction of property. The Desert Chupacabra is one of the worst.
Name: Dimension Desert Chupacabra

Description: Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life
Name: Dimension Varv

Description: While it has no eyes, Arma has a highly developed sense of hearing and smell.
Name: Dimension Arma

Description: It attacks people with the bead that it is holding every day.
Name: Dimension Dimmer

Description: A monster variant that comes from a wizard's belongings. It is resistive to its original use.
Name: Dimension Flask

Description: A sad monster that can't fly.
Name: Dimension Phyracon

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Shaman Doll

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Black Shaman Doll

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Wizard Shaman Doll

Description: The Slime is an organism in the demon realm. Its population exploded after the time when the plant cataclysm, especially around the Mage Tower.
Name: Dimension Experimental Slime

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complex. The number of Vubbe that are able to learn magic after Medzio Diena has greatly increased and their techniques are similar to that of earlier human wizards.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Wizard

Description: Vubbe Shaman only have meager powers and usually inspire other Vubbe through tattoos or drawings.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Shaman

Description: A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.
Name: Dimension Chromadog

Description: It is a monster that has the power of various animals, so it is hard to face against.
Name: Dimension Rambear

Description: Ultanuns have always been flightless birds even before their deformation.
Name: Dimension Ultanun

Description: Don't let its cute appearance fool you. This monster will try to tear you apart, given the chance.
Name: Dimension Rubabos

Description: A somewhat cute mutant that is always expressionless. They assemble together when chanting.
Name: Dimension Moya

Description: Moyabu has evolved from the Moya. It is more violent than the Moya.
Name: Dimension Moyabu

Description: When it comes to flight, Bavon would be better just floating there as is.
Name: Dimension Bavon

Description: A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.
Name: Dimension Tanu

Description: A three headed monster. It is hard to tell whether the main body is just one head or all three.
Name: Dimension Zignuts

Description: The demons have tamed Denden and use it for their means.
Name: Dimension Denden

Description: If a moving poisonous mushroom makes you anxious, consider Doyor as an example.
Name: Dimension Doyor

Description: The yellow grass on its body looks supple. But if you touch it, it can be quite painful .
Name: Dimension Tipio

Description: The Rondo is not an animal found in our world, rather it is an animal that crossed from the demon realm.
Name: Dimension Rondo

Description: Although it appears to have no sharp edges, it will when engaged in battle.
Name: Dimension Caro

Description: There are not too many cases of a fruit deformed monsters. Leafnut belongs to these few cases.
Name: Dimension Leafnut

Description: The flowers around its neck are actually real flowers rather than decorations.
Name: Dimension Mallardu

Description: You will face its relentless anger if you carelessly touch it.
Name: Dimension Mali

Description: Be aware of the smoke that this creature spurts as it is highly toxic and will last for a while.
Name: Dimension Grummer

Description: A bite from its sharp beak causes persistent pain, which may last for a while.
Name: Dimension Hummingbird

Description: The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.
Name: Dimension Leafly

Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.
Name: Dimension Vikaras Mage

Description: A moving tree monster that appeared after the Great Plant Cataclysm, it was named after its discoverer.
Name: Dimension Firent

Description: Galok is a monster who command workers in the demon realm.
Name: Dimension Galok

Description: Upent rapidly appeared from what once were flora with magical powers.
Name: Dimension Upent

Description: When the demons found Glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.
Name: Dimension Glizardon

Description: The Corylus is a mutant hybrid between plants, animals and minerals.
Name: Dimension Corylus

Description: The only good thing that came from the mutation was that the beast became a bit smaller. Also, the fact that someone had managed to capture one doesn't mean that it is any less dangerous. Loxodon of this color have usually feasted on strange food.
Name: Dimension Red Loxodon

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.
Name: Dimension Beeteros

Description: A mutated mantis. It has gotten stronger and has developed the ability to camouflage.
Name: Dimension Mantiwood

Description: Egnomes carry a stern look. The more stern it looks, the more powerful it is.
Name: Dimension Egnome

Description: A poet had once said that this monster is the fruition of a flower petal's dream of flying. Upon hearing this, the Sage Master said something about knowing when to be poetic and when to run.
Name: Dimension Beetow

Description: The sister of Pawnd. Carries a scythe that is much taller than itself. It's name depends on where and what it is born of.
Name: Dimension Pawndel

Description: Carcashu is a fungus. Its toxins are strong, but there are parts of it that can be eaten.
Name: Dimension Carcashu

Description: The fruit of a Maize looks quite tasty. Of course, you'll be poisoned if you actually decide to eat some. This color of Maize even has fungi that will make it even worse for anyone brave or stupid enough to try.
Name: Dimension Black Maize

Description: This monster was bred by the demons and is known for its poisonous abilities.
Name: Dimension Velwriggler

Description: Its appearance did not change much, but its physicality has. Lives near water.
Name: Dimension Ducky

Description: This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.
Name: Dimension Cronewt

Description: There are many birds that cannot fly after they've transformed to monsters.
Name: Dimension Infro Hoglan

Description: The Dumaro is not a newly discovered monster, but has developed new toxic abilities after the Great Plant Cataclysm.
Name: Dimension Dumaro

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Dimension Lichenclops

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Dimension Rubblem

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Dimension Loftlem

Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Blindlem

Description: Infroblood is a case where plant spores transform into monsters. It can float.
Name: Dimension Infro Blood

Description: By looking at the spear Ticen is carrrying, the assumption that there may be other kinds of Ticens turned out to be true, with many kinds of Ticens created now moving in herds. They care about sociality.
Name: Dimension Ticen

Description: A tip of Tucen's tail is made out of minerals.
Name: Dimension Tucen

Description: They consume either small animals or insects. Nevertheless, they show hostility to the animals that are bigger than them, so anyone who encounters with them should be careful.
Name: Dimension Colitile

Description: Although they are small, they are already hosts. Of course, they will keep growing.
Name: Dimension Minivern

Description: It is uncertain which roles Belegg is responsible for and whether they are just moving magical creatures.
Name: Dimension Belegg

Description: The Woodfung is closely related to witchcraft.
Name: Dimension Woodfung

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Dimension Red Infrorocktor

Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.
Name: Dimension Corrupt Vikaras Mage

Description: The bravest Vubbe Spearman are said to volunteer to become a Vubbe Scout. Some think that these Vubbe have actually been manipulated by the other Vubbe.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Scout

Description: Vubbe Archers show proficiency at using projectile weapons. This proficiency is used as evidence in pointing out that the Vubbe have specialized roles. Of course, there will always be rookies.
Name: Dimension Novice Vubbe Archer

Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Siaulamb Shaman

Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Siaulamb Lagoon

Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Siaulamb Warrior

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted.
Name: Dimension Yognome

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occured in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Siaulav

Description: A soldier that makes up the army of the demons.
Name: Dimension Pawnd

Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Big Siaulamb

Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.
Name: Dimension Siaulogre

Description: There's no one who wants to see the true nature of the hidden face behind this mask.
Name: Dimension Pendinmire

Description: It could be said that such a color comes from fungi latching onto a monster that is already a mutation of a different kind of fungi.
Name: Dimension Black Big Griba

Description: A popular theory is that you have to be a demon to use this messenger.
Name: Dimension Black Desmodus

Description: Pantos used to live at the Geli region from a long time ago and they kept their friendly relationship with humans before they were influenced on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Large Panto Spearman

Description: Vubbe Archers specialize in using ranged weapons. Thus some people claim the Vubbes have specific roles.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Archer

Description: Deadborns turn into Rodelins when they receive a lot of influences from demons or when they are acknowledged by the high-ranked demons.
Name: Dimension Rodelin

Description: The Tree Ambulo is not a mutation of a plant. In fact, it has it's origins in the demonic world. However, the demons to seem to think of it as some sort of pot plant.
Name: Dimension Red Tree Ambulo

Description: The Rondo is not a mutation from anything on our world. It's origins are in the demonic world. Those of this color have been affected by the volcanic eruption in the demonic world or are their descendants.
Name: Dimension Red Rondo

Description: You might think that the Rubabos are cute, but always beware that they can shred you to pieces. Rubabos that have had mutated food after Medzio Diena become a similar color.
Name: Dimension Red Rubabos

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Dimension Rusty Old Hook

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Dimension Yellow Gazing Golem

Description: It exhibits a much more stern expression than that of a Yognome. It is also that much stronger. Those affected by demons are of this color.
Name: Dimension Yellow Egnome

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted. Those that were affected by demonic energy are of this color.
Name: Dimension Yellow Yognome

Description: Unlike it's cute looks, it usually remains expressionless while ramming into you. Those of this color are known to have been affected by the demons.
Name: Dimension Yellow Moya

Description: Although it originates from an amphibian, it poses a great threat to travelers since it's mutation into a monster capable of hunting where there is no water. Thankfully, those of this color suffer from???rogeria and don't live long.
Name: Dimension White Groll

Description: The reason that a Dandel's down is more dangerous than keratin is because of it's increased energy and aggression. Thankfully, these Dandel don't have the capabilities to reproduce. Of course, there are mutated specimen after Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension White Dandel

Description: The reason that a Dandel's down is more dangerous than keratin is because of it's increased energy and aggression. Thankfully, Dandel of this color are weak during their molting period.
Name: Dimension Orange Dandel

Description: Although this monster's name might match up to it's appearance, it doesn't match it's personality at all. Geppetto of this color cannot reproduce.
Name: Dimension White Geppetto

Description: It is said that the Geppetto was named as such because they thought that it was related to the Pino. Those that are this color usually don't have reproductive capabilities.
Name: Dimension White Pino

Description: Operor are monsters that are unusually close to their original form, but have had their aggressiveness and violent tendencies enhanced. It is a specimen that had been in a coma after coming back from the demonic world.
Name: Dimension White Operor

Description: Carcashu???re the pufferfish of mushrooms. There are edible parts despite the toxins. This color of Carcashu can't live for more than a year.
Name: Dimension Green Carcashu

Description: Hamming are usually easy to handle, but do have an extremely hard outer skin. This color of Hamming becomes harder the more it sheds it's skin.
Name: Dimension Orange Hamming

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours. Those from Brimstonia are of this color.
Name: Dimension Orange Lizardman

Description: The Tama is also a monster that has mutated from the spore of a plant. It is unknown if whether it will mutate further from it's current form. Tama of this color have been affected by sulfur and have the possibility to mutate even further.
Name: Dimension Orange Tama

Description: Speculated to be a monster that the demon created by using a Chupacabra. It is unknown why there are specimen of this color.
Name: Dimension Pink Chupaluka

Description: Still has a tendency of going after rotten flesh. Those that have had their blood's color change after Medzio Diena show these colors.
Name: Dimension Orange Kowak

Description: Even though there are less logging activities, the monsters that originated from stumps continue to show up. They appear to be formed out of the residues of Plant-type monsters. Those of this color periodically lose a part of their bark and die earlier than others.
Name: Dimension Orange Stumpy Tree

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color shed their skin.
Name: Dimension Orange Siaulav

Description: This monster, which was born as a direct result of demonic influence, is agile and has poisons. Velwriggler that have been strongly affected by magic show these colors.
Name: Dimension Blue Velwriggler

Description: Has a tendency to respect strong opponents. Of course, this doesn't make much a difference since it is more violent toward weaker opponents and loves to challenge stronger ones. Those of this color are said to be suffering from the side effects of coming over from the demonic world.
Name: Dimension Blue Stoulet

Description: There are many birds that cannot fly after they've transformed to monsters.
Name: Dimension Red Infro Hoglan

Description: A monster derived from a spore which floats. Older specimen are known to be this color.
Name: Dimension Red Infro Blood

Description: A soldier that makes up the army of the demons.
Name: Dimension Black Pawnd

Description: The sister of Pawnd. Carries a scythe that is much taller than itself. It's name depends on where and what it is born of.
Name: Dimension Blue Pawndel

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Dimension Pure Loftlem

Description: Not a particularly strong monster, but you might end up crying if you attack it without thinking twice. Has a tendency of becoming red as it ages.
Name: Dimension Large Red Kepa

Description: It is hard to determine whether their mining roles are permanent since little is known about the Vubbe's social system.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Miner

Description: Colifly are the rookies of the demonic world, only appearing after Medzio Diena. They have yet to find their species' characteristics and are still in the process of creating societies but aren't looked down upon by other demons. Recently, there have been increases in individuals that have their own proficiencies such as magic.
Name: Dimension Black Colifly

Description: Colifly are the rookies of the demonic world, only appearing after Medzio Diena. They have yet to find their species' characteristics and are still in the process of creating societies but aren't looked down upon by other demons. Recently, there have been increases in individuals that have their own proficiencies such as magic.

Description: The difference between Kepos and Keposeeds is whether they are the hosts or the fluids. When you think about it, the difference between the hosts and the fluids might seem big, but except for the breeding ability, fluids are equally dangerous.
Name: Dimension Kepossed

Description: If the monsters that base their origins on plants have an ability to create their offsprings, insides are often not filled.
Name: Dimension Lomor

Description: The difference between Kepos and Keposeeds is whether they are the hosts or the fluids. When you think about it, the difference between the hosts and the fluids might seem big, but except for the breeding ability, fluids are equally dangerous.
Name: Dimension Kepo

Recently, there have been increases in individuals that have their own proficiencies such as magic.
Name: Dimension Colifly

Description: This has great academic importance. The fact that Gribaru of this color used to be fungi before shedding is an amazing feat.
Name: Dimension Orange Gribaru

Description: It is sad that we cannot see animals like Rabbees in their appearances from the past.
Name: Dimension Rabbee

Description: Eldigo listens to the orders of stronger monsters in order to survive. But, the opponents it faces are usually stronger so it often gets sacrificed.
Name: Dimension Eldigo

Description: Sockets used to live deep underground in our world as well as in the demonic world. It is one of the few monsters that existed before Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Socket

Description: Austeya goddess was upset that the insects which she controls transformed, and she was especially upset after looking at this monster's trasformed appearance. This monster is one of the reasons that Austeya goddess is very firm against the demons after Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Honeybean

Description: Austeya goddess was upset that the insects which she controls transformed, and she was especially upset after looking at this monster's trasformed appearance. This monster is one of the reasons that Austeya goddess is very firm against the demons after Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Honeymeli

Description: Eldigo???ollow the orders of stronger monsters in order to survive. However, many of them are still sacrificed since they usually fight stronger opponents. The Green Eldigo???s that color due to acquired protective colors which slightly increase it's survivability.
Name: Dimension Green Eldigo

Description: Despite looking quite similar, this monster has nothing to do with the Glass Mole. In fact, this monster is a mutation of a plant.
Name: Dimension Pink Root Mole

Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.
Name: Dimension Night Maiden

Description: The Terra Imp is quite mischievous. One should be aware of their belongings, as they might steal them.
Name: Dimension Terra Imp

Description: Goblins that used to live in certain areas for a long time enhance their attack abilities and adaptability.
Name: Dimension Mine Predator

Description: Goblins that used to live in certain areas for a long time enhance their attack abilities and adaptability.
Name: Dimension Mine Fire Mage

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated. The number of Vubbe that are able to learn magic after Medzio Diena has greatly increased and their techniques are similar to that of earlier human wizards. It is interesting to see whether they will be able to replicate human Cyromancer techniques.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Ice Wizard

Description: Vubbe Warriors have appeared in earnest after Medzio Diena and try to become stronger through various ways including the utilization of human technology.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Warrior

Description: Some scholars want to know how grown up Melatinuns are like. But, adventurers, masters and soldiers don't want to know about them and they don't want to see their appearances.
Name: Dimension Melatinun

Description: An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appears even in areas where Vubbes are not found.
Name: Dimension Earth Wood Goblin

Description: Crawling amongst the shadows of the forest, this monster has evolved greatly in size over time.
Name: Dimension Earth Bushspider

Description: Kepa age quickly at the expense of their strength. Be careful of its pungent odor, which has gotten stronger with age.
Name: Dimension Earth Old Kepa

Description: Ghosts affected by demons often change their appearance in a way similar to this.
Name: Dimension Earth Apparition

Description: Shredded is a demon monster that was derived from the by-product that results when you transform a monster into a powerful ghost.
Name: Dimension Earth Shredded

Description: There are some instances Deadborns was born from the shells the Deadborns molted out or from the parts that were seperated from the bodies due to injuries. The original Deadborns had the tendency to discriminate these newcomers and humans also distinguish them from the original ones.
Name: Dimension Earth Deadborn Scap

Description: Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Name: Dimension Earth Hallowventer

Description: Raffly keep hunting smaller insects even after their unfortunate mutation while coming from the demonic world. Unbearable behavior from a demon's point of view.
Name: Dimension Blue Raffly

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted.
Name: Dimension Confined Yognome

Description: A shrub monster that attacks by either firing its twigs or striking with its branches.
Name: Dimension Confined Long-Branched Tree

Description: A moving tree monster that appeared after the Great Plant Cataclysm, it was named after its discoverer.
Name: Dimension Confined Firent

Description: Which part is the main part from Ashrong's body? Although, it may not be a helpful information to battles, this may be interested for some people.
Name: Dimension Ashrong

Description: Which part is the main part from Cornuts' body? Although, it may not be a helpful information in battles, this may be interested for some people.
Name: Dimension Cornuts

Name: Dimension Papayam

Description: This monster obtained its legendary name due to its appearance. Other than that, this monster doesn't have anything special.
Name: Dimension Tripede

Description: This monster possesses scary fist power and tenacious aggressiveness. It's specialty of hiding well in other places has totally disappeared.
Name: Dimension Crocoman

Description: It is said that they receive their powers from human souls because they gather toward the injured.

Description: Ghosts affected by demons often change their appearance in a way similar to this.
Name: Dimension Earth Spectra

Description: It is said that Deadborn have a chance of becoming Rodelin if they are strongly influenced by demons or are recognized by high ranking demons. Those that have been under the demonic world's sun for too long are this color.
Name: Dimension Brown Rodelin

Description: Pantos used to live at the Geli region from a long time ago and they kept their friendly relationship with humans before they were influenced on Medzio Diena.

Description: Pantos used to live at the Geli region from a long time ago and they kept their friendly relationship with humans before they were influenced on Medzio Diena.

Name: Dimension Panto Archer

Description: A Panto variant with distinctively high intelligence. They often show up with the other Panto variants.
Name: Dimension Panto Wizard

Description: A Panto with excellent fighting skills and is one of the strongest subspecies in the forest.
Name: Dimension Panto Warrior

Description: It is a magic creature whose name comes from the wishes of a golem species.
Name: Dimension Karas Wizard

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.

Description: By looking at the spear Ticen is carrrying, the assumption that there may be other kinds of Ticens turned out to be true, with many kinds of Ticens created now moving in herds. They care about sociality.

Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.

Description: The reason that a Dandel's down is more dangerous than keratin is because of it's increased energy and aggression. Thankfully, Dandel of this color are weak during their molting period.

Description: It has no relation with the Kepa. They are demonic beasts even if they do have a rather high intelligence.

Description: Spion usually follow their masters well if trained properly. Of course, most of their masters are demons. Spion Mages are usually born because they have received more power from their masters.

Description: While the bottom class of the demon world, their thirst to live better lives is almost frightening.

Description: Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours.

Description: While it has maintained its original form, Operor has developed severely aggressive and violent behavior.
Name: Dimension Operor

Description: Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Name: Dimension Hallowventer

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Dimension Ellomago

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Dimension Old Hook

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted.
