Description: There are some instances Deadborns was born from the shells the Deadborns molted out or from the parts that were seperated from the bodies due to injuries. The original Deadborns had the tendency to discriminate these newcomers and humans also distinguish them from the original ones.
Name: Dimension Deadborn Scap

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.
Name: Dimension Beeteros

Description: A monster that hates humans for unknown reasons. It will pick attacking humans over surviving or feeding. Truffle of this color loves to eat fungi from their own bodies.
Name: Dimension Blue Truffle

Description: Chupacabras appear simultaneously in various places and are threatening many lives and crops.
Name: Dimension Corrupt Chupacabra

Description: Operor are monsters that are unusually close to their original form, but have had their aggressiveness and violent tendencies enhanced. They have minuscule hairs.
Name: Dimension Blue Operor

Description: Ghosts affected by demons often change their appearance in a way similar to this.
Name: Dimension Red Apparition

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.
Name: Dimension Tala Wizard

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Archers have been affected more by demons, at least in theory.
Name: Dimension Tala Archer

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected, when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places with divine energy that humans do not know about.
Name: Dimension Tala Captain

Description: The Lyecorn is a monster that transformed from a fossilized plant and is therefore very unique.
Name: Dimension Lyecorn

Description: Lakhorn are monsters that appeared from the underworld where humans are not able to go to and have managed to emerge above ground.
Name: Dimension Lakhorn

Description: Lakhtanon are said to have been born in underground lakes or rivers. However, there are traces of civilization on them. There are people that say that this is because humans used to live underground a long time ago.
Name: Dimension Lakhtanon

Description: Lakhof are minerals from underground rivers that transformed on Medzio Diena. They have managed to come above ground since then.
Name: Dimension Lakhof

Description: The Lakhof is a monster derived from a mineral that had been near an underground spring. It came aboveground after Medzio Diena. Those of this color were affected by sulphur when they were underground.
Name: Dimension Orange Lakhof

Description: They had been left on the demons' side when the Goddesses and demons set new boundaries. They still have their old look about them, but their personalities have become much more demon-like.
Name: Dimension Bunkeyto

Description: The Tuthrycon will be able to live anywhere as long as it doesn't get pushed aside by it's competition. It's large mouth and teeth will allow it to obtain food easily.
Name: Dimension Tuthrycon

Description: The Nukhalong will occasionally eat other plant type monsters. This is more like vegetation using other plants as fertilizer than the hunting of predators.
Name: Dimension Nukhalong

Description: Although it is covered in leaves, this monster had started as steel ore that transformed on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Horned Golem

Description: When the Goddess' and demons were dividing borders, they were left on the demon's side simply by coincidence. While they have retained similar appearances, their personalities have already become in-sync with demons. They even play shamanic roles to demons that live in the outer areas. Normally known to assist other demons in preparing for Giltine's rituals.
Name: Dimension Romplenuka

Description: There are quite a few animals that gained the ability to fly when they transformed to monsters. Some say that this was due to their boredom of life on the ground.
Name: Dimension Mourningbird

Description: It has become stronger in exchange for losing its limbs when transforming into a monster.
Name: Dimension Nabu

Description: They had been left on the demons' side when the Goddesses and demons set new boundaries. They still have their old look about them, but their personalities have become much more demon-like.
Name: Dimension Bunkeybo

Description: It thrives in cold weather despite being an insect after transforming into a monster.
Name: Dimension Mouringaka

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Dimension Vylkhas

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Dimension Vylkhas Assassin

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Dimension Vylkhas Mage

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Dimension Vylkhas Spearman

Description: People seem to think that the Vilkas despise humans, but they actually despise all other species.
Name: Dimension Vylkhas Archer

Description: According to legend, Minos used to fight between themselves. This is because the demon lords used to use them to keep the Minos of other demon lords in check. Minos that are treated well by high ranking demons are this color.
Name: Dimension Green Minos

Description: It is more accurate to say that the Bavon levitates rather than flies. Bavon of this color have plant-like characteristics which means that it can go a long while without eating.
Name: Dimension Green Bavon

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Dimension Green Rubblem

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Dimension Green Flamme

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Dimension Green Flamme Mage

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Dimension Green Zolem

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Dimension Green Flamag

Description: This species was formed hundreds of years ago when Gesti was ordered by Giltine to hunt for the revelation. Many Flamme were deployed in various areas on Gesti's orders after Medzio Diena. They say that Gesti prefers this color of Flamme.
Name: Dimension Green Flamme Archer

Description: A type of demon summoned by Vubbe at the bidding of demons. It also appears where there are no Vubbe through unknown means. Those of this color cannot live for more than a year.
Name: Dimension Green Wood Goblin

Description: They had started to form a union when Gesti received the mission from Giltine to chase after the revelation. Since Medzio Diena, Flammes were created until then and their subspecies were dispatched to various places according to their creator, Gesti's order.
Name: Dimension Green Flak

Description: They had started to form a union when Gesti received the mission from Giltine to chase after the revelation. Since Medzio Diena, Flammes were created until then and their subspecies were dispatched to various places according to their creator, Gesti's order.
Name: Dimension Green Flamil

Description: A monster derived from a demonic world frog. It is hard to speculate what the original form might have been due to the heavy mutation. This protective color helps if survive.
Name: Dimension Green Charog

Description: It's unsure that the demons ignore these monsters and use for the firewood by sacrificing.
Name: Dimension Green Charcoal Walker

Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Green Blindlem

Description: There are surprisingly few monsters that are derived from fruits. The Leafnut is such a monster. Some Leafnuts fulfill their roles as fruits when they die, but Yellow Leafnuts contaminate the ground making it impossible for vegetation to grow there.
Name: Dimension Yellow Leafnut

Description: Grummer can spew extremely toxic fumes that last a long time. As such, special care is required. Grummer of this color have poison from leaf mold.
Name: Dimension Orange Grummer

Description: They show tribunal characteristics which is exceptional among Plant-type monsters. In an academic point of view, many people wonder whether they would possess more sociality. Older Colimen turn this color.
Name: Dimension Red Colimen

Description: It looks like it doesn't have any sharp edges, but you might be surprised when fighting it. This color of Caro will hide underground during cold weather.
Name: Dimension Yellow Caro

Description: Take a look at the Doyor if you want to know what a moving poisonous mushroom looks like. Doyor of this color will live for 2 or 3 years.
Name: Dimension Blue Doyor

Description: Tanu are insect-eating plants that have mutated to be meat-eating plants. Tanu of this color have long life expectancies for such plants.
Name: Dimension Blue Tanu

Description: Polibu eat small animals, insects and even dead bodies. They even attack humans to simply have one bite so you should be cautious. Polibu of this color hibernate.
Name: Dimension Yellow Polibu

Description: It is commonly thought to be a monster derived from a hedgehog, but nobody is quite certain. There are quite a few scholars that suggest it is derived from vegetation. Gosaru of this color live longer than average.
Name: Dimension Blue Gosaru

Description: A poet had once said that this monster is the fruition of a flower petal's dream of flying. Upon hearing this, the Sage Master said something of knowing when to be poetic and when to run. Beetow of this color are usually domesticated.
Name: Dimension Blue Beetow

Description: While it's appearance hasn't changed much, it's characteristics have changed dramatically. Does not need to live near water anymore. Some have become this color after eating vegetation on land.
Name: Dimension Red Ducky

Description: A beast that thrives even in the demonic world which is now terrorizing our world. Those suffering from the side effects of dimensional travel are of this color.
Name: Dimension Blue Moglan

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Dimension Green Ellomago

Description: A monster summoned by demonic world Shamans by using a Luwa. There are also unconfirmed rumors that they used a Wood Spirit. Those of this color are usually summoned by powerful Shaman even if they are weak.
Name: Dimension Blue Woodluwa

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Dimension Green Goblin Warrior

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Dimension Green Goblin Charger

Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. As reference, Woodgoblins and Goblins are not directly related.
Name: Dimension Green Goblin Wizard

Description: Medzio Diena changed environments to be more hospitable towards Goblins. They have grown in numbers to the point of taking over much of what used to be human territory. Wood Goblins have nothing to do with normal Goblins. Goblin Shamans held advisory roles in Goblin society even before Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Green Goblin Shaman

Description: A monster made by demons using a Goddess Statue that has lost it's divine powers. Those of this color are usually made from statues that had been in shady areas.
Name: Dimension Black Shardstatue

Description: Lower ranking demons in the demonic world that have a strong desire to rise through the ranks. These Templeslaves will soon be promoted.
Name: Dimension Black Templeslave

Description: Lower ranking demons in the demonic world that have a strong desire to rise through the ranks. These Templeslaves will soon be promoted.
Name: Dimension Black Templeslave Assassin

Description: The fruits of a Maize look quite appetizing. Of course, you will be poisoned if you actually eat any. Such fruits become this color if nobody actually picks them.
Name: Dimension Red Maize

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are usually older than the rest.
Name: Dimension Red Siaulav

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are infested by fungi.
Name: Dimension Black Siaulav Archer

Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occurred in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans. Those of this color are infested by fungi.
Name: Dimension Black Siaulav Mage

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Dimension Red Slime

Description: While it can't see, it is much more agile than it looks since it has great hearing and smelling capabilities. Those that have been strongly affected by demons are of this color.
Name: Dimension Yellow Arma

Description: The Pyran are born from reptilian eggs that are buried under ash. Those from Brimstonia are this color.
Name: Dimension Yellow Pyran

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Red Wizard Shaman Doll

Description: The Rodejokel is a foot soldier of the Rode society.
Name: Dimension Rodejokel

Description: The Nuttabug has extremely slow metabolism and will search for a new fruit when it devours it's current fruit. It will die if it cannot find a suitable fruit in time, but this is extremely rare due to it's slow metabolism.
Name: Dimension Nuttabug

Description: The Rhodenabean are common folk in the Rhode society and will use whatever is in their hands as weapons.
Name: Dimension Rhodenabean

Description: Rhodenags are usually workers. They use their tools to pick fruit or work the soil.
Name: Dimension Rhodenag

Description: They are mainly specialized workers of the Rhode, but will sometimes use attacks related to their work.
Name: Dimension Rhodetad

Description: Usually storage keepers for the Rhode.
Name: Dimension Elder Rhode

Description: They are treated the worst in the Rhode society. They like to compensate for that by decorating themselves in lavish ways.
Name: Dimension Rhodedoe

Description: They can be seen as the freaks of the Rhode society.
Name: Dimension Rhodeliot

Description: It is said that the Nuttabug will become Nuttafly???f they manage to survive long enough.
Name: Dimension Nuttafly

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Tots will never betray anyone that they have a connection to. The issue is that they don't seem to make connections with humans.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Tot

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Sommi usually like to be revered by others and will help those that revere them.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Sommi

Description: Other Kugheri will often ride or use it to transport luggage.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Lyoni

Description: The connection of Numani is incomparable to others. They only respect those that are spiritually stronger than themselves.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Numani

Description: There are rumors that say that you will be able to befriend a Symbani if you manage to save its life.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Symbani

Description: The Zabbi do the occasional biddings of Kugheri Numani and wait for the chance to become Numani themselves.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Zabbi

Description: The mental state of Kugheri Zeuni has not been properly recorded anywhere.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Zeuni

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. The only way to resolve a feud with a Balzer is to kill it or be killed.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Balzer

Description: The Zeffi are small but have murderous intent behind their every move.
Name: Dimension Kugheri Zeffi

Description: You might think that the Ragbird doesn't look like much. You may want to think again taking in the fact that it's a demon.
Name: Dimension Ragbird

Description: Although it was overshadowed by stronger demons in demon territory, it is showing that it can be a terror of it's own here in our world.
Name: Dimension Ragged Butcher

Description: Did they raise crops in the demonic world and were they affected by Medzio Diena? Nobody knows, but it is an interesting topic to think about.
Name: Dimension Straw Walker

Description: It is impossible to tell if it is a real scarecrow or a monster. It might look similar because a demon might have imitated a human scarecrow. It might also be a mutation from the demonic world, but nobody knows for certain.
Name: Dimension Scarecrow

Description: What passes for a cute puppy in the demonic world is a savage beast by human standards.
Name: Dimension Amberdog

Description: A monster that has transformed from a poisonous flower that used to grow in dark places.
Name: Dimension Flowlon

Description: Many herbivores had been near their food on Medzio Diena and this caused them to have complex transformations. This is one of those monsters.
Name: Dimension Flowlevi

Description: Bloms and Virdneys became monsters through the same process. The only difference is that Virdneys sprouted from the ground.
Name: Dimension Virdney

Description: A monster that has transformed from a flower or fruit that was still on its original branch.
Name: Dimension Blom

Description: Nothing is known about Anchors except that they are from the demonic world. It is unknown if an object became a monster or if it is a mutated demon. Even the colors do not offer any proper evidence.
Name: Dimension Red Anchor

Description: They murder demon soldiers if they get bored. It is said that those of this color are favored by Kartas.
Name: Dimension Green Prison Fighter

Description: Akhlass type monsters are demons, but originate from our world. The Akhlass Dame has re-transformed itself after gaining human essence.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Dame

Description: The armor of Akhlass Tikke shows what the Tikke wishes to become. The estrangement is somewhat saddening.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Tikke

Description: The Akhlass absorb human essence when they become demons. By doing so, they acquire desires that they don't have as bats. This is much more common among Beorns than Tikke.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Beorn

Description: Akhlass Sensors enjoy absorbing and emitting the energy of demons. They become stronger through this process.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Sensor

Description: Unlike other Akhlass, the Humps do not have any aspirations related to humans. They believe that humans must cease to exist as there is nothing else to be learned from them.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Hump

Description: The Akhlass Petals wish to become a Countess by proving their worth. As such, they also like to order those around as much as they like to fight themselves.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Petal

Description: Akhlass Steel have a tendancy to fight as they wish instead of following the orders of others.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Steel

Description: The Akhlacia are not as high up the hierarchy as they initially seem. They are more like maids for nobles. In other words, their class is in accordance to their owner.
Name: Dimension Akhlacia

Description: All Akhlass Bishops are ambitious and will scheme about climbing the demon social ladder at any chance.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Bishop

Description: The Countess has extremely good hearing even among the Akhlass. It is said that they are able to hear conversations that others can't hear.
Name: Dimension Akhlass Countess

Description: It is little ambiguous which types of lives become the source of Gaigalas. It is suspicious if they existed in our world.
Name: Dimension Gaigalas

Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.
Name: Dimension Golem

Description: Current Ginklas is caught by madness, so there is no chance to show his original rationality.
Name: Dimension Ginklas

Description: It was never observed before that a monster which was originally a bug turned into an imago type monster. It shouldn't occur when you look at it.
Name: Dimension Ravinepede

Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or if they are originally demonic beings. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.
Name: Dimension Rajatoad

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Dimension Rikaus

Description: It is known that the tail is used when they compete against each other, but you should not just rely on such tendency.
Name: Dimension Mallet Wyvern

Description: Even the demons who caused Medzio Diena didn't know the Magburks around them would turn out like this.
Name: Dimension Magburk

Description: For unknown reasons, after mutating during Medzio Diena this monster shows high hostility towards the goddesses.
Name: Dimension Mushcaria

Description: Some of the monsters have strong powers by changing the format at Medzio Diena tried to make a cooperation with Demon or hired by them.
Name: Dimension Bearkaras

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Fighter

Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.
Name: Dimension Red Vubbe Fighter

Description: Demon Lord Bramble is considered the least ingenious. Gesti, who favors simpler personalities, however, granted him higher authority. Bramble is also believed to have nearly succeeded in seizing a goddess relic, a task where other Demon Lords have failed.
Name: Dimension Bramble

Description: Insect-type monsters mutated during Medzio Diena are known to have queens or other monarch entities.
Name: Dimension Biteregina

Description: Basically, It was born in the cold region, after Medzio Diena, it is actively working around because spotted in many areas.
Name: Dimension Saltistter

Description: Although its name is not unique, this monster in fact will is the most faithful companion of death that you will encounter.
Name: Dimension Scorpio

Description: Yekub unleashes its infamous cry in the demon realm, which produces many minions and spreads them around the world. Yekubite is the name given to these minions.
Name: Dimension Yekub

Description: The advantage can be found the powerful monsters are that many of them can't move to another place.
Name: Dimension Iltiswort

Description: The forest became horror after Medzio Diena. It mainly caused by the large scale monsters to be hard to defeat.
Name: Dimension Giant Red Wood Goblin

Description: Although it does not affect humans, this monster strongly dislikes other insect types besides itself, particularly bee-type monsters.
Name: Dimension Chafer

Description: The research to find out why some Kepas transformed like this is ongoing. There are also efforts to make them edible, but not many expect positive results.
Name: Dimension Kepa Chieftain

Description: Before Medzio Diena, encounters humans rarely encountered Hydras, but when they did, the Hydras were an opponent difficult to face. They are no longer imortal, however, so anyone competent enough should be able to hunt one.
Name: Dimension Hydra

Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or if they are originally demonic beings. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.
Name: Dimension Rajapearl

Description: Old Status that Goddess' divinity left from here will absorb the demons.
Name: Dimension Corrupted

Description: As a bird, it is easily attracted to bird feed. Demons use this to make these monsters attack humans.
Name: Dimension Sparnas

Description: Although its name is similar, it is not related to the monsters that turned out from birds.
Name: Dimension Sparnasman

Description: Since the Pantos turned their backs on humans, the species that were never seen before appeared. Maybe... the demons are the culprit.
Name: Dimension Capria

Description: Prior to Medzio Diena, this monster spent most of its time sleeping, so it wasn't that dangerous.
Name: Dimension Nepenthes

Description: Naktis has three sisters who are Demon Lords and they are all related to Demon Queen Gesti.
Name: Dimension Naktis

Description: Neop was recently promoted as a Demon Lord by Giltine in order to disturb Laima's plans. Because of the promotion, he tries hard to learn more.
Name: Dimension Neop

Description: The Tetraox used to be a beast used in arenas before Medzio Diena. As such, they not only hate Gladiators and Matadors, but ordinary humans as well.
Name: Dimension Tetraox

Description: This was a monster that threatened the human society a long time ago. When Roxona turned into a petrified city, there was a rumor that there was a herd of Basilisks.
Name: Dimension Basilisk

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Dimension Gremlin

Description: Velnewts usually group together and hunt together at the demon realm. But, they think that they are strong enough to act alone in our world so they tend to act individually.
Name: Dimension Velnewt

Description: There are many monsters of this kind in the demon realm and the Demon Lord picks the strong ones among them and releases them to our world.
Name: Dimension Velpede

Description: Sadly, many strong-spirited people have sided with the demons after Medzio Diena. I believe this is an issue that requires a proper policy of tactical negotiation.
Name: Dimension Pyroego

Description: This arrogant monster who betrayed the blessing of Goddess Zemyna is considered a shame to the goddesses.
Name: Dimension Lithorex

Description: This cruel lord of the flowers tries to control all lives in the region he controls regardless whether they are animals or plants.
Name: Dimension Nuodai

Description: Progola???ack sociability, even for a demon. They are forced to work by stronger demons. Before Medzio Diena, they used to hide in order to escape this forced labor.
Name: Dimension Progola

Description: Marionette is a monster that looks familiar, but brings fear from that familiarity.
Name: Dimension Marionette

Description: This transformation is now considered ordinary, in a world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.
Name: Dimension Crabil

Description: While most fairy or spirit-type creatures have sided not with humans and goddesses but with demons, the small minority that hasn't is currently taking a neutral stance. Genies are one type of such creatures.
Name: Dimension Master Genie

Description: This info might not be useful to you in real battles, but this monster is very weak against other demons.
Name: Dimension Grinender

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Dimension Gazing Golem

Description: The demons are controlling the strong ones among the creatures that turned into monsters on Medzio Diena. Gorgon used to exist even before Medzio Diena, but it's form and the habit is different from the past.
Name: Dimension Gorgon

Description: The Glackuman, who dreams of becoming a famous fighter, is only satisfied if he is dispatched to locations where a lot of fights are taking place.
Name: Dimension Glackuman

Description: There's a rumor that the monster who Rexipher modified to break into the Royal Mausoleum is the starting point.
Name: Dimension Glass Mole

Description: Nederbovine bases its origin on the demon realm. This is not an intelligent demon. It is a beast that is being raised by demons.
Name: Dimension Netherbovine

Description: He has the tendency to control evil spirits and steal the power from those who do not obey him in order to accumulate even greater power.
Name: Dimension Necroventer

Description: Nuaele is one of those low-ranked Demon Lords. Strangely enough many demons follow it so that other Demon Lords do not treat them lightly.
Name: Dimension Nuaele

Description: Usually referred to as a monster that returned from the dead. In reality, it underwent death to be reborn as a demon.
Name: Dimension Deadborn

Description: Legend has it that this is an object of an ancient devil whose identity is unknown. According to that legend, even Giltine didn't want to fight against it.
Name: Dimension Devilglove

Description: The history of the Deathweaver has long been known to humans. Many are the warriors and mages who perished in their nets of death.
Name: Dimension Deathweaver

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Baiga uses. Baiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Dimension Denoptic

Description: Dullahan was one of the ghosts that was known to the human world and there were some kinds among them that do not harm people that are not related to the resentment. But, as you know, Medzio Diena changed everything.
Name: Dimension Dullahan

Description: When Rocktortuga first appeared, many soldiers had difficulties retreating due to it's stubborness. As time went by, the weakness on its body was made known, but it's not easy to attack weakness of Rocktortuga.
Name: Dimension Rocktortuga

Description: In the past this animal was quite friendly towards humans, but now it's even more dangerous than demons.
Name: Dimension Lepus

Description: Rexipher is known as the wisest Demon Lord among all Demon Lords. The reason why he is not active as he should be is because the Demon Queen Gesti doesn't know how to use him effectively. That is good for humans.
Name: Dimension Rexipher

Description: When it succeeds in suppressing an opponent, it has the tendency to paralyze the opponent and suck the body fluid of the opponent at a slow pace. After it increases its size, it attacks small-sized opponents to relieve its aggression and not to fulfill its hunger.
Name: Dimension Reaverpede

Description: There's a legend were Riteris was one of the masters in the past. Among the masters that are not wizards, some make contracts with the demons for immortality and look for others who are similar to them, then lead them to the demon realm.
Name: Dimension Riteris

Description: The theory that Linkrollers move by magical reaction has been proven. However, what's interesting is that this was not designed by anyone, it was simply created naturally around Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Linkroller

Description: Giltine thought that Demon Queen Gesti was not working as expected as she dispatched the many Demon Lords recently. Marnox is a recent typical Demon Lord.
Name: Dimension Marnox

Description: It is unclear whether it was mutated during Medzio Diena or through a Demon Lord ritual. In any case, it was once a useful piece of equipment.
Name: Dimension Mineloader

Description: He has four strong arms. If you don't be careful, you may receive major damage.
Name: Dimension Mandara

Description: The demons are trying to give the Manticen great power so they can control other insect-type monsters.
Name: Dimension Manticen

Description: In theory, this monster's creation is similar to Dullahan. However, the combined object is not a shield.
Name: Dimension Mummyghast

Description: The monster which was transformed by demons after combining diverse types of creatures still shows its loyalty to the demons.
Name: Dimension Merge

Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.
Name: Dimension Mothstem

Description: Among the ones who try to tame many different kinds of birds, many of them are not interested in Moas. Because this bird eats too much.
Name: Dimension Moa

Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Moyabruka

Description: Humans and monsters have the tendency to harass others that are weaker than them.
Name: Dimension Moldyhorn

Description: Molich has served several Demon Lords over the centuries and is likely to keep advancing into higher ranks. Experts who have studied demon history predict that, if he does, he could surpass even lower-rank Demon Lords such as Bramble or Mirtis.
Name: Dimension Molich

Description: Minotaurs have existed since a long time ago, and besides the fact that one other species with wings came from it, they remain as violent as they were in the past.
Name: Dimension Minotaur

Description: Mirtis is considered a low-ranked Demon Lord of all the others. The reason why is probably because she failed many missions that were given to her from Giltine. On her last mission, she was sealed by a human. Since Medzio Diena, she has now the freedom to catch up on her failed mission.
Name: Dimension Mirtis

Description: Humans have attempted to tame these monsters before they grow, but only demons have succeeded in doing so.
Name: Dimension Bebraspion

Description: You shouldn't just think of it as a beast of the demons. This monster is actually intelligent!
Name: Dimension Velnia Monkey

Description: They are the demons who took care of the garden of high-ranked demons and fruit trees. After Giltine decided to fight against the goddesses, they now participate in battles. Like most other demons, what they do and their battle skills and all are unrelated.
Name: Dimension Velorchard

Description: There's nothing special about Demon Lord Blut. But, what is significant about him is that he is the Demon Lord that was randomly picked by Giltine to disturb Laima's prediction.
Name: Dimension Blut

Description: The ones who were known as strong warriors in the demon realm stepped into our world because of Giltine's orders.
Name: Dimension Cyclops

Description: A monster that already existed before Medzio Diena. It used to have a liking towards humans in the past, but that feeling has faded away in the current times.
Name: Dimension Salamander

Description: Shadowgaler was originally a spirit, but it embraced the power of the demons on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Shadowgaler

Description: As a monster of mineral-type mutation, it is unclear why it bears resemblance to a whale.
Name: Dimension Stone Whale

Description: It was created to protect humans by Dievdirbys Master, but it has been the harmful monsters to change the characteristtics.
Name: Dimension Sequoia

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Dimension Shnayim

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Dimension Specter Monarch

Description: Simorph was reported as the first case that obtained the status of a demon as a monster due to its cooperation. Some masters don't want this to be the example of future unpleasant outcomes.
Name: Dimension Simorph

Description: Powerful insect-type monsters tend to become either vicious hunters or influential individuals. The latter group, in which the Throneweaver is included, is particularly dangerous, as they often side with demons.
Name: Dimension Throneweaver

Description: There's a rumor going around that Ironbaum used to be the target of practice for the demons. Regardless of what their origin is, they are threats to us now.
Name: Dimension Ironbaum

Description: Archon belongs to a high class in the demon realm and he is responsible for many things besides the battles.
Name: Dimension Archon

Description: At first, they were created accidentally through the abuse of magic, but later malicious wizards and demons started creating them intentionally.
Name: Dimension Abomination

Description: It is the creation of magic that mages and humans frequently used to protect their treasures.
Name: Dimension Unknocker

Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.
Name: Dimension Achat

Description: Ellaganos are undead creatures that become fused with their gravestones and emerge after a long period of time possessing enormous power.
Name: Dimension Ellaganos

Description: Yeti was just a legend prior to Medzio Diena and it's appearance was discovered only recently which led to it's acknowledgment as a monster.
Name: Dimension Yeti

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Dimension Yonazolem

Description: They can be called the Bokors of the demon realm. It is possible that they interact with Giltine and use the authority.
Name: Dimension Wood Houngan

Description: Werewolves have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.
Name: Dimension Werewolf

Description: The Divine Tree, which was the rest place for the goddesses, became their enemy.
Name: Dimension Unicorn

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Dimension Zaura

Description: An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appears even in areas where Vubbes are not found.
Name: Dimension Giant Wood Goblin

Description: It is known that Chapparitions were being created when the spirits of dead mages fell into evil deeds.
Name: Dimension Chapparition

Description: Many monsters created lots of diverse transformations on Medzio Diena, but Carapace is unique among them. It was created from the shell which was molted from other animals.
Name: Dimension Carapace

Description: The transformation of the Canceril is now considered ordinary, in a world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.
Name: Dimension Canceril

Description: Among the spirits of the forest, it is sad that the ones who were most close to the humans became the enemies of the humans.
Name: Dimension Centaurus

Description: Compared to the goddesses, the demons either grow or create demons that protect their territories. According to a legend, Cerberus didn't have the form it now has.
Name: Dimension Cerberus

Description: Initially, many people underestimated Colimencia, a strong Plant-type monster, since it was in a state of inactivity, but they received severe damage.
Name: Dimension Colimencia

Description: Rexipher tried many times to infiltrate into the royal tomb. He didn't succeed the infiltration, but he was able to make a monster called Kubas.
Name: Dimension Kubas

Description: It likes to hide in dark places or deep forests. It is timid so it only appears and attacks when it thinks the opponent is weak.
Name: Dimension Clymen

Description: Kirmeleech sucks the blood of either monsters or demons since humans are too small for them. However, they do not attack humans, so it's actually not important whether they suck blood from humans or not.
Name: Dimension Kirmeleech

Description: The most dramatic change the Goblin society experienced on Medzio Diena was the appearances of strong creatures like the Templeshooter. However, they prioritize their individual benefits more than the Goblin tribe. Even if they serve others, there's a certain possibility that they have hidden purposes.
Name: Dimension Templeshooter

Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.
Name: Dimension Tutu

Description: A long time ago, he was the hidden guardian who used to protect graves from robbers.
Name: Dimension Tomb Lord

Description: This monster who betrayed Goddess Gabija can be called the heretic of the spirits.
Name: Dimension Fire Lord

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Dimension Ferret Marauder

Description: Poata is trying to find chances to showoff to the demons to obtain more power from the monsters originated plants.
Name: Dimension Poata

Description: Violence and cruelty is normal in this place so it's a perfect place for demons. They enjoyed tortures and killings in the demon realm.
Name: Dimension Prison Cutter

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Dimension Flammidus

Description: It is a creature that places its origin to the demon realm. It is a kind that is related to Velnewt.
Name: Dimension Plokste

Description: Though it is a legend that cannot be confirmed, but Harpeia used to follow Goddess Laima instead of the demons.
Name: Dimension Harpeia

Description: It became ever more difficult for Goddess Austeja to look over this task, and so this type of monsters started to appear.
Name: Dimension Honeypin

Description: Helgasercle used to be one of the strongest Demon Lords out there. Hauberk who was also the Demon Lord who received her wrath and was sealed after she showed her powers. It is not strange that Agailla Flurry is praised by many as the greatest mage in history since she fought against Helgasercle for hundreds of years and won.
Name: Dimension Helgasercle

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Dimension Specter of Deceit

Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.
Name: Dimension Gray Golem

Description: A subspecies of the Hanaming. Recently found and currently still in research.
Name: Poiming
